1
00:00:00,167 --> 00:00:02,302
- Really?
- Is this the right way?

2
00:00:02,302 --> 00:00:03,403
This should be fun.

3
00:00:04,338 --> 00:00:05,672
It looks so elegant.

4
00:00:06,673 --> 00:00:09,243
- Let's go together.
- I don't think we're allowed.

5
00:00:09,243 --> 00:00:10,878
It says you need to be over 65.

6
00:00:10,878 --> 00:00:12,012
Sir.

7
00:00:12,012 --> 00:00:14,181
- Hello!
- Welcome.

8
00:00:14,181 --> 00:00:16,083
Oh, but...

9
00:00:16,083 --> 00:00:17,184
What a shame.

10
00:00:17,885 --> 00:00:19,987
[It's A Senior Café]

11
00:00:19,987 --> 00:00:22,289
[But A Crowd Of Children Has Arrived]

12
00:00:22,289 --> 00:00:23,557
- You can look around.
- Of course.

13
00:00:23,557 --> 00:00:25,158
- Take a look.
- Go ahead.

14
00:00:25,158 --> 00:00:26,360
[Visiting From The School Next Door]

15
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:27,461
Come inside.

16
00:00:27,461 --> 00:00:28,862
- Hello.
- Hello.

17
00:00:29,363 --> 00:00:30,631
Hi.

18
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:35,502
The kids probably want to eat it.
What do we do?

19
00:00:35,502 --> 00:00:36,670
I know, right?

20
00:00:36,670 --> 00:00:37,671
I feel so bad.

21
00:00:39,106 --> 00:00:40,173
Looks good, right?

22
00:00:40,173 --> 00:00:43,115
Go and bring your grandparents.

23
00:00:43,577 --> 00:00:44,811
You can eat here then.

24
00:00:44,811 --> 00:00:47,714
So, only people over 65 can eat here?

25
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:51,752
You can eat here
if you come with a senior.

26
00:00:51,752 --> 00:00:53,387
Can I bring my dad?

27
00:00:53,387 --> 00:00:56,290
Your dad is probably too young.

28
00:00:56,290 --> 00:00:57,991
- He's 50 years old.
- Not possible.

29
00:00:57,991 --> 00:00:59,359
No can do.

30
00:00:59,359 --> 00:01:00,694
What a shame.

31
00:01:00,694 --> 00:01:02,829
- He's not even close.
- Take a picture with them.

32
00:01:02,829 --> 00:01:04,865
I'll take a picture with you.

33
00:01:04,865 --> 00:01:07,267
But he's more popular than me.

34
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:08,669
He's from Seventeen.

35
00:01:08,669 --> 00:01:09,636
Hello.

36
00:01:09,636 --> 00:01:11,905
You know him, don't you?

37
00:01:12,773 --> 00:01:15,409
[Amazed By Who He Is]

38
00:01:15,409 --> 00:01:17,711
[Clap]
He's very popular.

39
00:01:17,711 --> 00:01:19,212
[Seventeen's Song]
Who?

40
00:01:19,212 --> 00:01:20,447
- Clap?
- Clap.

41
00:01:20,447 --> 00:01:22,049
Yes, thank you.

42
00:01:22,049 --> 00:01:23,050
[One Of Seventeen's Mega-Hit Songs]
That's right.

43
00:01:23,050 --> 00:01:26,153
- Do you want a picture with both of us?
- Yes, please.

44
00:01:26,153 --> 00:01:27,354
All of us.

45
00:01:27,354 --> 00:01:28,755
Okay, come here.

46
00:01:30,223 --> 00:01:33,560
Should we go outside
so you can see the sign?

47
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:36,209
- Great idea.
- Let's go outside.

48
00:01:40,901 --> 00:01:42,869
- Come to the front.
- Let's move closer together.

49
00:01:42,869 --> 00:01:44,404
- Come closer.
- Closer.

50
00:01:44,404 --> 00:01:45,672
[A Customer Joins Them]
Okay, ready.

51
00:01:45,672 --> 00:01:47,674
One, two, three.

52
00:01:48,742 --> 00:01:50,143
[Bonjour Bakery]

53
00:01:50,143 --> 00:01:53,146
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

54
00:01:53,146 --> 00:01:54,681
Bye.

55
00:01:54,681 --> 00:01:56,483
Take care.

56
00:01:56,483 --> 00:01:58,085
[Ordered To Go]

57
00:01:58,085 --> 00:02:01,855
[Complimentary Jam]
Please have it with this jam.

58
00:02:01,855 --> 00:02:04,524
- Okay, thank you.
- Thank you.

59
00:02:11,498 --> 00:02:13,767
[The Customers Have Left]

60
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:17,971
- Is this almost done?
- There is one minute left.

61
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:20,407
We wrap it and let it rest.

62
00:02:20,407 --> 00:02:22,509
Tear off each piece and roll it out.

63
00:02:22,509 --> 00:02:24,845
[Checking The Loaf Dough]
We'll fold it three times today.

64
00:02:24,845 --> 00:02:26,913
It seems good. Just a minute.

65
00:02:26,913 --> 00:02:27,981
Let me try.

66
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:29,082
[Cha Loaf Bread Dough]

67
00:02:31,652 --> 00:02:34,121
You have to be able
to see your fingerprint.

68
00:02:34,121 --> 00:02:35,222
[Does The Dough Stretch Smoothly?]

69
00:02:35,222 --> 00:02:38,425
[Also Known As The Window Test]

70
00:02:38,425 --> 00:02:40,160
I think I did a good job.

71
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:42,010
Right? It looks good.

72
00:02:50,804 --> 00:02:53,807
[Ferment At Room Temperature For 50 Minutes]

73
00:02:53,807 --> 00:02:58,311
[Cover With Plastic To Maintain Consistent
Moisture And Temperature]

74
00:03:00,647 --> 00:03:05,519
[Meanwhile, Someone's Stuck With Washing Dishes]

75
00:03:06,453 --> 00:03:08,522
- Thanks for your hard work.
- Sorry?

76
00:03:08,522 --> 00:03:10,991
You were called in so suddenly.

77
00:03:10,991 --> 00:03:11,992
Don't mention it.

78
00:03:11,992 --> 00:03:14,174
I'm fine since I have you.

79
00:03:15,395 --> 00:03:17,831
I don't know what I'm doing either.

80
00:03:17,831 --> 00:03:20,567
- We'll face this together.
- Yes.

81
00:03:20,567 --> 00:03:22,936
[The Hall Team Is Growing
Through Challenges]

82
00:03:24,771 --> 00:03:27,507
Sorry, but what does Dino mean?

83
00:03:27,507 --> 00:03:29,009
- My name?
- Yes.

84
00:03:29,009 --> 00:03:30,343
From the word "dinosaur."

85
00:03:30,343 --> 00:03:32,913
- Dinosaur?
- Yes, the shortened form of it.

86
00:03:32,913 --> 00:03:34,848
- I see.
- Why is it a dinosaur?

87
00:03:34,848 --> 00:03:37,651
It means I'm powerful on stage.

88
00:03:37,651 --> 00:03:40,554
[Embarrassed]
Kind of that vibe.

89
00:03:40,554 --> 00:03:41,722
What's your real name?

90
00:03:41,722 --> 00:03:43,190
It's Lee Chan.

91
00:03:43,190 --> 00:03:45,959
- Lee Chan?
- Yes, I remember now.

92
00:03:45,959 --> 00:03:48,318
That's a cool name.

93
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:50,831
Is there a sweet drink?

94
00:03:50,831 --> 00:03:53,066
- A sweet drink?
- Yes, something really sweet.

95
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:55,569
- We have an orangeade.
- Perfect.

96
00:03:55,569 --> 00:03:56,703
[Sugar Crash After Prep]
Is it quick to make?

97
00:03:56,703 --> 00:03:58,772
- Can I get a cup of that?
- Okay.

98
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:06,046
[Serious When Making Drinks]

99
00:04:06,046 --> 00:04:09,216
She goes quiet when she's doing this.

100
00:04:09,216 --> 00:04:10,117
I was like that.

101
00:04:10,117 --> 00:04:14,755
[Words Disappear With Focus]
I was measuring things and went quiet.

102
00:04:16,456 --> 00:04:17,858
It's ready.

103
00:04:22,996 --> 00:04:23,997
It's really good.

104
00:04:24,698 --> 00:04:27,000
- It's good even without sugar, right?
- It's delicious.

105
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,448
It's perfect.

106
00:04:32,072 --> 00:04:33,306
This is really great.

107
00:04:33,306 --> 00:04:36,209
[Proud]

108
00:04:36,209 --> 00:04:37,778
[On Break]

109
00:04:37,778 --> 00:04:40,247
[You Must Be Over 65 Years Old To Enter]

110
00:04:42,249 --> 00:04:46,987
[The Senior Locals Gather]

111
00:04:46,987 --> 00:04:51,591
[At The Village Hall For Lunch]

112
00:04:51,591 --> 00:04:53,660
- We should have lunch.
- Yes.

113
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:54,995
What should we get?

114
00:04:54,995 --> 00:04:56,730
[Break Time Is Lunch Time]
In our fridge...

115
00:04:56,730 --> 00:04:59,366
There were frozen hot dogs and stuff.

116
00:04:59,366 --> 00:05:00,967
[Simple Lunch For Day One?]
We could have those.

117
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:04,237
What should we eat? Let me check.

118
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:15,749
[What's In Here?]

119
00:05:18,018 --> 00:05:20,320
[What Did He Take Out?]

120
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:23,356
[It's Kimchi!]

121
00:05:23,356 --> 00:05:24,257
What's this?

122
00:05:24,257 --> 00:05:27,027
I thought I'd make kimchi stew.

123
00:05:27,027 --> 00:05:29,196
You must be tired, though.

124
00:05:29,196 --> 00:05:31,731
[Today's Lunch Is Kimchi Stew]

125
00:05:31,731 --> 00:05:34,467
What are you adding?

126
00:05:34,467 --> 00:05:37,537
- Some pork.
- Pork?

127
00:05:37,537 --> 00:05:39,105
I'm happy just watching.

128
00:05:39,105 --> 00:05:42,108
[What Is The Kimchi Stew Recipe?]

129
00:05:42,108 --> 00:05:44,945
[Cut The Kimchi Haphazardly]

130
00:05:45,445 --> 00:05:48,321
[Add A Little Bit Of Kimchi Brine]

131
00:05:48,321 --> 00:05:51,958
[Add Some Chili Peppers For Spiciness]

132
00:05:52,652 --> 00:05:56,923
[Add Lots Of Pork]

133
00:05:56,923 --> 00:05:59,459
He's too tall for the sink.

134
00:05:59,459 --> 00:06:00,527
What?

135
00:06:00,527 --> 00:06:02,796
- This is more comfortable.
- Of course.

136
00:06:02,796 --> 00:06:06,132
[A Posture To Protect His Back]
It hurts to bend down when you're tall.

137
00:06:06,132 --> 00:06:09,302
[Add Water]

138
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:12,305
[Add Tuna Fish Sauce For The Flavor]

139
00:06:12,305 --> 00:06:13,960
We have to boil it for a while.

140
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:15,041
A long time.

141
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:17,878
The longer you boil it, the better.

142
00:06:17,878 --> 00:06:19,479
[Unlike Delicate Baking,
A Quick Kimchi Stew Is Whipped Up]

143
00:06:21,815 --> 00:06:27,888
[Let's Make A Delicious Kimchi Stew]

144
00:06:27,888 --> 00:06:31,024
I was going to make fried eggs,

145
00:06:31,024 --> 00:06:35,295
but they stuck to the frying pan.

146
00:06:35,295 --> 00:06:38,865
Then let's add a little water

147
00:06:38,865 --> 00:06:42,302
and cover it to make poached eggs.

148
00:06:42,302 --> 00:06:44,471
How about that?

149
00:06:44,471 --> 00:06:45,972
Add a little salt.

150
00:06:45,972 --> 00:06:48,074
[Hee Ae Makes Poached Eggs]

151
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:50,043
I'm just trying to cook it well.

152
00:06:50,043 --> 00:06:53,546
I feel nervous when you're watching.

153
00:06:53,546 --> 00:06:54,881
I'll leave.

154
00:06:54,881 --> 00:06:58,068
I'm just making it so we can have it.

155
00:07:01,021 --> 00:07:06,793
[Countless Eggs Are Added]

156
00:07:07,227 --> 00:07:08,788
Okay.

157
00:07:09,896 --> 00:07:11,610
Oh, dear.

158
00:07:12,165 --> 00:07:14,000
[Poached Eggs?]

159
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:18,438
[Egg Soup?]

160
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:21,508
Are you sure?

161
00:07:21,508 --> 00:07:22,976
- Is it weird?
- What?

162
00:07:22,976 --> 00:07:25,712
The whites broke apart.

163
00:07:25,712 --> 00:07:27,514
You have to add it one by one.

164
00:07:27,514 --> 00:07:30,917
[Embarrassed]
Then they're not poached eggs.

165
00:07:30,917 --> 00:07:33,153
[Eggs That Were Supposed To Be Poached]

166
00:07:33,153 --> 00:07:35,088
Do you have to film this?

167
00:07:35,088 --> 00:07:37,090
Don't film this.

168
00:07:37,090 --> 00:07:40,932
I've never made so many at once.

169
00:07:42,662 --> 00:07:44,164
[Chuckles]

170
00:07:45,165 --> 00:07:47,801
I'm going to get scolded.

171
00:07:49,803 --> 00:07:54,240
[Rescues The Poached Eggs For Now]

172
00:07:58,511 --> 00:08:00,513
Chef Cha!

173
00:08:00,513 --> 00:08:02,249
- Chef Cha.
- Yes?

174
00:08:02,249 --> 00:08:04,403
I messed up.

175
00:08:07,187 --> 00:08:11,003
It was crazy of me
to try to cook in front of you.

176
00:08:13,626 --> 00:08:14,661
What about rice?

177
00:08:14,661 --> 00:08:16,730
We can have those.

178
00:08:18,331 --> 00:08:19,833
Simple meals.

179
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,701
[Instant Rice For Convenience]

180
00:08:22,235 --> 00:08:23,970
This is all done.

181
00:08:23,970 --> 00:08:25,705
The kimchi stew is ready.

182
00:08:25,705 --> 00:08:27,240
[The Kimchi Stew Got Ready In The Meantime]

183
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:38,318
It looks amazing.

184
00:08:38,318 --> 00:08:39,853
[The Kimchi Stew]

185
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:42,355
They're mushy now.

186
00:08:42,355 --> 00:08:46,659
[That Chef Cha Whipped Up]

187
00:08:48,294 --> 00:08:50,230
- Sorry.
- Don't worry about it.

188
00:08:50,230 --> 00:08:52,165
[And Eggs Served With An Apology]
Two eggs per person.

189
00:08:52,165 --> 00:08:53,782
Thank you.

190
00:08:55,135 --> 00:08:56,269
Thank you.

191
00:08:56,269 --> 00:08:57,670
Sorry.

192
00:08:57,670 --> 00:08:59,806
Thanks for the meal.

193
00:09:01,841 --> 00:09:04,677
I'll give you the one
that looks poached, Chef Cha.

194
00:09:04,677 --> 00:09:06,424
Thank you so much.

195
00:09:08,014 --> 00:09:09,582
This looks great.

196
00:09:09,582 --> 00:09:12,685
- Thanks for the meal.
- Let's dig in.

197
00:09:12,685 --> 00:09:14,071
Let's see.

198
00:09:15,722 --> 00:09:19,959
[A Bite Of Hee Ae's Poached Eggs First]

199
00:09:19,959 --> 00:09:21,728
It's good.

200
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:23,457
Seriously.

201
00:09:24,197 --> 00:09:26,466
- I'm serious.
- It's delicious.

202
00:09:29,202 --> 00:09:31,037
Maybe it's the seasoned salt.

203
00:09:31,037 --> 00:09:32,705
This is great. Thank you.

204
00:09:32,705 --> 00:09:34,061
Bon appetit.

205
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:39,179
We definitely needed the eggs, didn't we?

206
00:09:39,179 --> 00:09:40,543
Yes.

207
00:09:43,450 --> 00:09:45,552
- I'm excited.
- What?

208
00:09:45,552 --> 00:09:47,079
For the stew.

209
00:09:55,662 --> 00:09:57,230
- This is so good.
- Really?

210
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:59,165
That's all I need.

211
00:09:59,165 --> 00:10:02,102
How is it, Hee Ae?

212
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:03,254
Earlier,

213
00:10:04,304 --> 00:10:05,972
the cabbage was fresh,

214
00:10:05,972 --> 00:10:09,679
but you managed
to make it like aged kimchi.

215
00:10:11,344 --> 00:10:12,612
This is amazing.

216
00:10:18,552 --> 00:10:20,453
- This is delicious.
- Really?

217
00:10:20,453 --> 00:10:22,285
- Yes.
- That's good to hear.

218
00:10:25,825 --> 00:10:27,727
This is really good.

219
00:10:27,727 --> 00:10:30,066
- This one.
- Thank you.

220
00:10:30,730 --> 00:10:32,065
What is it?

221
00:10:32,065 --> 00:10:33,169
Scallion kimchi.

222
00:10:33,169 --> 00:10:34,968
Ki Taek brought it.

223
00:10:34,968 --> 00:10:36,769
[The Side Dishes Ki Taek Brought]

224
00:10:37,937 --> 00:10:39,661
Did your mother make this?

225
00:10:39,661 --> 00:10:40,740
Yes, she did.

226
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:42,242
- By herself?
- Yes.

227
00:10:42,242 --> 00:10:46,913
She made it when she heard about you guys.

228
00:10:46,913 --> 00:10:48,848
I hope it's to your liking.

229
00:10:52,552 --> 00:10:54,287
The scallion kimchi is so good.

230
00:10:54,287 --> 00:10:56,122
Thank you, Hee Ae.

231
00:10:57,137 --> 00:11:00,765
- Thank you.
- Your mother went above and beyond.

232
00:11:03,596 --> 00:11:05,165
How was the meal, Dino?

233
00:11:05,165 --> 00:11:06,799
It was really good.

234
00:11:06,799 --> 00:11:11,738
You came to help
without knowing what it was for.

235
00:11:11,738 --> 00:11:13,206
Still...

236
00:11:13,206 --> 00:11:15,008
He did great today.

237
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:17,836
- Right?
- Yes, he handled everything calmly.

238
00:11:18,545 --> 00:11:20,146
- Thank goodness.
- Yes.

239
00:11:20,813 --> 00:11:22,048
[Bonjour Bakery]

240
00:11:22,048 --> 00:11:24,050
- Thanks for the meal.
- Thank you.

241
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:26,619
- Thank you.
- That was really delicious.

242
00:11:26,619 --> 00:11:27,921
[Let's Work Hard!]

243
00:11:35,195 --> 00:11:38,464
[Today's Menu]

244
00:11:38,464 --> 00:11:42,368
[Chan Adds Items To The Afternoon Menu]

245
00:11:42,368 --> 00:11:46,139
[Bonjour Green Barley Choux]

246
00:11:46,940 --> 00:11:49,275
Good job!

247
00:11:51,878 --> 00:11:57,150
[3 Items Are Added To The Menu]

248
00:11:57,150 --> 00:12:01,221
[Bonjour Green Barley Choux]

249
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:04,891
[Bonjour Vanilla Choux]

250
00:12:04,891 --> 00:12:08,695
[Bonjour Cha Loaf Bread]

251
00:12:09,295 --> 00:12:15,001
[The Morning Menu Is Also Available]

252
00:12:17,370 --> 00:12:26,212
[Ki Taek Stocks Afternoon Desserts]

253
00:12:36,489 --> 00:12:39,192
[Day 1 Afternoon Hours Begin Now!]

254
00:12:43,129 --> 00:12:48,101
[1st Proof Complete
Divide Into 280g Portions]

255
00:12:50,871 --> 00:12:52,872
[Divide Into 280g Portions]
Two hundred eighty grams.

256
00:12:52,872 --> 00:12:54,741
About this much.

257
00:12:54,741 --> 00:12:57,910
This should be a bit over 280 grams.

258
00:12:57,910 --> 00:12:59,512
Three hundred.

259
00:12:59,512 --> 00:13:00,813
[Dividing The Dough]

260
00:13:00,813 --> 00:13:02,682
[Is A Matter Of Meticulous Precision]

261
00:13:02,682 --> 00:13:04,617
Two hundred sixty.

262
00:13:05,351 --> 00:13:07,253
[The Goal Is 280g]

263
00:13:11,357 --> 00:13:13,159
Two hundred eighty.

264
00:13:13,159 --> 00:13:15,401
I'll set it aside.

265
00:13:16,329 --> 00:13:18,931
[Won't Allow More Than A 1-Gram Margin Of Error!]

266
00:13:24,837 --> 00:13:28,808
[The Journey For 280g]

267
00:13:28,808 --> 00:13:30,043
All done.

268
00:13:30,043 --> 00:13:31,844
[Flatten And Round]

269
00:13:31,844 --> 00:13:34,747
[Each 280g Piece Of Dough]

270
00:13:48,428 --> 00:13:51,130
[Group Into 6]

271
00:13:51,130 --> 00:13:53,399
[And Proof For 20 Minutes]
Twenty minutes.

272
00:13:53,399 --> 00:13:55,568
These look delicious.

273
00:13:55,568 --> 00:13:58,137
[Proofing]

274
00:14:00,039 --> 00:14:02,210
Time goes by so slowly.

275
00:14:02,742 --> 00:14:04,344
I think it's done.

276
00:14:04,344 --> 00:14:07,213
[It May Seem Like It's Done]

277
00:14:07,213 --> 00:14:09,416
[But The Real Work Begins Now]

278
00:14:09,416 --> 00:14:14,455
[Once The Dough Has Proofed
Shape It To Fit The Tins]

279
00:14:15,321 --> 00:14:16,656
[Roll The Dough Into An Oval]

280
00:14:16,656 --> 00:14:18,191
This should be good.

281
00:14:19,158 --> 00:14:22,995
[Fold The Top And Bottom Thirds
Toward The Center]

282
00:14:24,931 --> 00:14:28,334
[Then Give It Another Roll]

283
00:14:31,204 --> 00:14:33,940
[Tuck The Corners In]

284
00:14:35,174 --> 00:14:37,110
[Then Pinch The Seams Shut]

285
00:14:38,111 --> 00:14:39,178
[Repeat 5-Step Shaping Process Twice]

286
00:14:39,178 --> 00:14:41,047
[Repeat 5-Step Shaping Process Twice
For One Loaf Of Bread]

287
00:14:44,784 --> 00:14:46,819
[Working On His 6th Piece]

288
00:14:49,489 --> 00:14:51,324
[Once They're In The Tins]

289
00:14:51,324 --> 00:14:53,459
[Time For The Next Batch]
Here.

290
00:14:53,459 --> 00:14:54,293
Put it there.

291
00:14:56,062 --> 00:14:57,063
Pass me that.

292
00:14:58,263 --> 00:14:59,599
It looks delicious.

293
00:15:04,036 --> 00:15:07,273
This is like a nightmare.

294
00:15:07,273 --> 00:15:09,275
It's a nightmare.

295
00:15:09,275 --> 00:15:10,810
[Obediently Rolling The Dough As He Speaks]

296
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:13,153
It's Bonjour Nightmare.

297
00:15:16,315 --> 00:15:18,217
[The Bread Devil Has Appeared]

298
00:15:38,070 --> 00:15:40,206
[After Shaping The Dough 24 Times]

299
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:44,143
It's a nightmare.

300
00:15:44,143 --> 00:15:45,912
[Nightmare Ceremony]

301
00:15:48,881 --> 00:15:52,652
[Final Proof For 1 Hour And 40 Minutes]

302
00:15:52,652 --> 00:15:54,720
- Welcome.
- Hello.

303
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:55,721
[Kim Il Nam, Im Yang Taek]

304
00:15:55,721 --> 00:15:58,524
- Would you like me to explain?
- Yes, please.

305
00:15:58,524 --> 00:15:59,625
Something not too sweet.

306
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:01,160
Not too sweet?

307
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:03,062
How about the Sweet Potato Cake?

308
00:16:03,062 --> 00:16:05,164
- Yes, that's a good one.
- Sounds good.

309
00:16:05,164 --> 00:16:08,501
- It's the least sweet one here.
- Okay.

310
00:16:08,501 --> 00:16:09,669
This is the Sweet Potato Cake.

311
00:16:09,669 --> 00:16:10,899
We'll have that.

312
00:16:10,899 --> 00:16:11,971
All right.

313
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:13,706
- We'll take two.
- Two pieces of cake.

314
00:16:13,706 --> 00:16:15,141
Okay.

315
00:16:15,141 --> 00:16:17,010
- It'll be right out.
- Okay.

316
00:16:17,510 --> 00:16:18,878
[Bonjour Bakery]

317
00:16:19,579 --> 00:16:21,647
[Bonjour Sweet Potato Cake]

318
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:23,850
[A Delicate French Mousse Meets]

319
00:16:23,850 --> 00:16:25,785
[Gochang Sweet Potato]

320
00:16:25,785 --> 00:16:27,954
[Gochang Sweet Potato
Grown In Mineral-Rich Red Soil And Sea Air]

321
00:16:27,954 --> 00:16:31,824
[For Maximum Sweetness]

322
00:16:33,926 --> 00:16:38,197
[Line The Mold With 1cm Sweet Potato Slices]

323
00:16:38,197 --> 00:16:40,166
[Mousse Made From Pureed Sweet Potato]

324
00:16:42,368 --> 00:16:44,303
[Fill In Every Corner]

325
00:16:45,438 --> 00:16:47,707
[And Spread Into A Thick Layer]

326
00:16:48,975 --> 00:16:51,611
[Top It With A Sponge Cake And Let It Set]

327
00:16:57,550 --> 00:17:00,853
[Finish With Glaze For Shine And Moisture]

328
00:17:14,667 --> 00:17:17,706
Bonjour Sweet Potato Cake.

329
00:17:17,706 --> 00:17:18,738
Green barley!

330
00:17:18,738 --> 00:17:20,406
No, that's wrong.

331
00:17:20,406 --> 00:17:21,774
I forgot the name.

332
00:17:21,774 --> 00:17:23,943
- That was amazing.
- You did great.

333
00:17:23,943 --> 00:17:25,611
- It's cake.
- That was awesome.

334
00:17:25,611 --> 00:17:27,280
- Green barley.
- Great job.

335
00:17:27,780 --> 00:17:30,716
Are young people not allowed here?

336
00:17:32,218 --> 00:17:34,220
They have to bring

337
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:40,060
- someone over 65 if they want to come.
- I just realized you're Kim Hee Ae.

338
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:41,996
- You're right.
- My goodness.

339
00:17:42,495 --> 00:17:44,497
- I'm sorry for not recognizing you.
- It's okay.

340
00:17:44,497 --> 00:17:46,166
- You came this far.
- Yes.

341
00:17:46,166 --> 00:17:49,735
- I thought you looked familiar.
- Same here.

342
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:52,405
- You came all this way.
- I'm a big fan.

343
00:17:52,405 --> 00:17:54,240
- I really am.
- Thank you.

344
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:57,410
- I'm such a fan.
- Thank you for coming.

345
00:17:57,410 --> 00:17:59,478
You're in great shape, ma'am.

346
00:17:59,478 --> 00:18:03,149
I hope nothing's bothering your health.

347
00:18:03,149 --> 00:18:05,384
- I have diabetes and high blood pressure.
- You have diabetes.

348
00:18:05,384 --> 00:18:07,453
- My goodness.
- I have a lot of health conditions.

349
00:18:07,453 --> 00:18:10,456
I see. What a shame.

350
00:18:10,456 --> 00:18:11,824
Thank you for coming.

351
00:18:11,824 --> 00:18:13,326
- Thank you.
- Have a seat.

352
00:18:13,326 --> 00:18:14,994
- Thank you.
- My goodness.

353
00:18:14,994 --> 00:18:18,864
I thought I recognized you.

354
00:18:18,864 --> 00:18:21,200
You know what?

355
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:24,403
[A Character Played By Kim Hee Ae]
I loved your role as Hu Nam.

356
00:18:24,403 --> 00:18:26,973
- You remember that?
- Of course.

357
00:18:26,973 --> 00:18:30,787
That was almost 40 years ago.
It was in 1993.

358
00:18:31,844 --> 00:18:32,979
My goodness.

359
00:18:32,979 --> 00:18:34,080
[Takes A Bite]

360
00:18:42,989 --> 00:18:44,991
- Previously...
- Let's share this.

361
00:18:44,991 --> 00:18:47,360
- Let's save that for your husband.
- Is it sweet?

362
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:49,795
It's not too sweet. Try it.

363
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:53,299
[Sneak]

364
00:18:53,299 --> 00:18:55,334
I don't feel like it.

365
00:18:55,334 --> 00:18:57,937
At least try a bite.

366
00:18:57,937 --> 00:19:01,173
I can't finish all this, so have some.

367
00:19:01,173 --> 00:19:02,975
I can't finish all this.

368
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:05,711
- You can take one to go.
- Yes.

369
00:19:05,711 --> 00:19:07,813
We'll wrap it up for you.

370
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:11,917
I'm just not feeling very good today.

371
00:19:17,523 --> 00:19:21,027
I did something stupid today.

372
00:19:21,027 --> 00:19:22,495
I'm starting to feel upset.

373
00:19:22,495 --> 00:19:25,831
Don't say something like that.

374
00:19:25,831 --> 00:19:30,336
That's just how life goes sometimes.

375
00:19:31,137 --> 00:19:34,782
I only held back because of you.

376
00:19:41,614 --> 00:19:43,949
You're getting teary again.

377
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:50,715
I'll take a loaf of bread.
Please ring us up.

378
00:19:51,692 --> 00:19:53,126
You're leaving already?

379
00:19:56,162 --> 00:19:58,731
- I'll pay for everything.
- Okay.

380
00:19:58,731 --> 00:20:00,900
[Wants To Repay The Warmth She Received]
Let's see...

381
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:02,301
I'll ring you up.

382
00:20:02,301 --> 00:20:03,669
Please insert your card.

383
00:20:03,669 --> 00:20:04,637
[Secretly Paying For Everything]

384
00:20:05,337 --> 00:20:07,406
- Why are you leaving so soon?
- What?

385
00:20:09,108 --> 00:20:10,843
We have work to do at home.

386
00:20:10,843 --> 00:20:13,279
- Are you paying for everything?
- Yes.

387
00:20:13,279 --> 00:20:14,547
We'll pay separately.

388
00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:16,382
- No, it's on me.
- Just split it.

389
00:20:16,382 --> 00:20:18,451
- It's fine.
- No.

390
00:20:18,451 --> 00:20:20,052
- Let me pay for you.
- You're all set.

391
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:21,754
You split it, right?

392
00:20:21,754 --> 00:20:23,689
No, it was one payment.

393
00:20:23,689 --> 00:20:26,092
- I'll pay.
- Just leave it.

394
00:20:26,092 --> 00:20:28,561
- Let me pay for mine.
- It's fine.

395
00:20:28,561 --> 00:20:30,896
We should pay separately.

396
00:20:30,896 --> 00:20:32,098
Just leave it.

397
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:35,034
Did you have some coffee?

398
00:20:35,034 --> 00:20:36,001
No, we didn't.

399
00:20:36,001 --> 00:20:38,604
- We don't drink coffee.
- I understand.

400
00:20:38,604 --> 00:20:41,207
I was so surprised when I heard

401
00:20:41,207 --> 00:20:44,443
- how old she is.
- How old are you?

402
00:20:44,443 --> 00:20:45,878
I was born in 1946.

403
00:20:45,878 --> 00:20:47,413
- Then...
- She's...

404
00:20:47,413 --> 00:20:49,281
She's 81.

405
00:20:49,281 --> 00:20:51,657
- You're...
- She doesn't look her age.

406
00:20:52,418 --> 00:20:55,921
You're in such great shape, ma'am.

407
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:57,490
I'm not in great shape.

408
00:20:57,490 --> 00:21:00,326
My knees have been working up lately.

409
00:21:00,326 --> 00:21:02,394
Since my knees hurt,

410
00:21:02,394 --> 00:21:06,732
[Complaining About Knees]
I feel kind of depressed.

411
00:21:06,732 --> 00:21:08,925
I've seen all your shows.

412
00:21:09,969 --> 00:21:11,437
Thank you.

413
00:21:11,437 --> 00:21:14,373
- Thank you.
- Be careful not to shake it too much.

414
00:21:14,373 --> 00:21:17,443
It will lose its shape if it topples over.

415
00:21:17,443 --> 00:21:18,778
- Okay.
- Good.

416
00:21:18,778 --> 00:21:19,945
Here's the bread.

417
00:21:19,945 --> 00:21:22,114
- I added jam, so please eat it together.
- Okay.

418
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:23,582
Thank you.

419
00:21:23,582 --> 00:21:26,018
If you're not eating
the Sweet Potato Cake,

420
00:21:26,018 --> 00:21:29,288
be sure to seal it
when you refrigerate it.

421
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:31,791
- Please be sure to do that.
- All right.

422
00:21:31,791 --> 00:21:34,260
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

423
00:21:34,260 --> 00:21:35,761
- Goodbye.
- Thank you.

424
00:21:35,761 --> 00:21:37,329
- Take care.
- Bye.

425
00:21:37,329 --> 00:21:39,298
- Get home safely.
- Thank you.

426
00:21:40,432 --> 00:21:42,001
Take care.

427
00:21:42,001 --> 00:21:48,007
[We Hope This Helps Your Gloomy Day]

428
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:55,347
[There's A New Bakery In Our Neighborhood?]

429
00:21:55,347 --> 00:21:57,883
[Bonjour Bakery]

430
00:22:02,621 --> 00:22:05,758
[We Heard The News!]

431
00:22:06,559 --> 00:22:08,027
- Hello.
- Hi.

432
00:22:08,027 --> 00:22:10,362
- Hello.
- Welcome.

433
00:22:11,030 --> 00:22:13,699
[My Goodness]

434
00:22:13,699 --> 00:22:15,100
Hello.

435
00:22:16,735 --> 00:22:18,137
Thank you, ma'am.

436
00:22:18,137 --> 00:22:19,905
- Welcome.
- My goodness.

437
00:22:23,375 --> 00:22:28,113
[Preparing Warm Towels For The Customers]

438
00:22:28,113 --> 00:22:33,786
The entry is restricted to those over 65.

439
00:22:33,786 --> 00:22:34,920
Yes.

440
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:38,858
[Asking Gently]
Could I please check your IDs?

441
00:22:38,858 --> 00:22:40,492
[Smiles]
Of course you can.

442
00:22:40,492 --> 00:22:42,061
You're not 65 years old.

443
00:22:42,061 --> 00:22:43,796
I wish I wasn't 65.

444
00:22:43,796 --> 00:22:46,098
Only one person has to be over 65.

445
00:22:46,098 --> 00:22:47,766
- I'm the youngest here.
- We're all young.

446
00:22:47,766 --> 00:22:50,402
- I thought you looked a bit young.
- Here you go.

447
00:22:50,402 --> 00:22:51,737
Okay.

448
00:22:51,737 --> 00:22:53,072
Thank you.

449
00:22:53,072 --> 00:22:54,673
You look so young.

450
00:22:54,673 --> 00:22:56,709
- Right?
- Thank you.

451
00:22:57,676 --> 00:22:59,812
Would you like me to explain?

452
00:22:59,812 --> 00:23:01,847
- Yes.
- Go ahead.

453
00:23:01,847 --> 00:23:04,350
- The first page is the drinks.
- Okay.

454
00:23:04,350 --> 00:23:06,118
There are tea and ade.

455
00:23:06,118 --> 00:23:07,853
What about the vanilla latte?

456
00:23:07,853 --> 00:23:09,355
They're available.

457
00:23:09,355 --> 00:23:11,323
We'll have four of those.

458
00:23:11,323 --> 00:23:12,925
- Vanilla latte?
- Yes.

459
00:23:12,925 --> 00:23:14,960
- Four vanilla lattes.
- Yes.

460
00:23:14,960 --> 00:23:16,962
- We'll also take desserts.
- Okay.

461
00:23:16,962 --> 00:23:19,164
We've got Green Barley Choux.

462
00:23:19,164 --> 00:23:20,499
I also recommend Vanilla Choux.

463
00:23:20,499 --> 00:23:22,835
Okay, we'll have four of those.

464
00:23:22,835 --> 00:23:25,938
- How about two of each choux?
- All right.

465
00:23:25,938 --> 00:23:27,806
- Sounds good.
- Okay.

466
00:23:27,806 --> 00:23:30,376
- Thank you.
- That's great.

467
00:23:30,376 --> 00:23:33,625
- Isn't the vanilla latte sweet?
- Yes.

468
00:23:34,179 --> 00:23:37,082
Sorry to keep asking this,

469
00:23:37,082 --> 00:23:39,451
but the vanilla latte is sweet.

470
00:23:39,451 --> 00:23:40,920
It's very sweet.

471
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:43,923
But the dessert is sweet as well.

472
00:23:43,923 --> 00:23:45,524
Are you okay with that?

473
00:23:45,524 --> 00:23:47,826
We'll have something that isn't sweet.

474
00:23:47,826 --> 00:23:49,535
- Without sugar, right?
- Yes.

475
00:23:49,535 --> 00:23:50,696
Me too.

476
00:23:50,696 --> 00:23:54,133
- I think a less sweet drink is better.
- Okay.

477
00:23:54,133 --> 00:23:56,535
- A latte that isn't sweet.
- Okay.

478
00:23:57,036 --> 00:23:59,471
[Hee Ae's Consideration For The Elderly]

479
00:24:00,139 --> 00:24:02,474
[You're The Best]

480
00:24:03,275 --> 00:24:05,311
Okay, café lattes.

481
00:24:05,311 --> 00:24:06,712
Finally, a latte.

482
00:24:06,712 --> 00:24:07,813
[I Can Do This]

483
00:24:10,916 --> 00:24:13,652
[Grind The Beans]

484
00:24:16,322 --> 00:24:18,958
[Get The Next One Ready]

485
00:24:23,329 --> 00:24:24,730
Keep calm.

486
00:24:26,765 --> 00:24:28,701
Eight o'clock, six o'clock.

487
00:24:28,701 --> 00:24:31,804
[Extracting The Coffee
Like Seon Ho Taught Him To]

488
00:24:43,749 --> 00:24:45,884
- Hi.
- Hello.

489
00:24:45,884 --> 00:24:47,786
- Have a seat.
- Nice to meet you.

490
00:24:47,786 --> 00:24:49,855
Nice to meet you.

491
00:24:49,855 --> 00:24:53,292
[Grandma And Granddaughter Take A Seat]

492
00:24:54,426 --> 00:24:58,497
Let's see. What should we get?

493
00:24:58,497 --> 00:25:00,165
[Bong Byeong Nam, Jung Chan Min]

494
00:25:00,165 --> 00:25:01,834
This one looks delicious.

495
00:25:01,834 --> 00:25:03,969
What else do you want with this?

496
00:25:03,969 --> 00:25:05,004
[Picked The Choux]

497
00:25:05,938 --> 00:25:08,540
[Everyone's Waiting For The Afternoon Dessert!]

498
00:25:09,942 --> 00:25:12,878
[The Vibrant Freshness Of Gochang's Green Barley]

499
00:25:13,779 --> 00:25:17,016
[Paired With A Crisp, Nutty Cookie]

500
00:25:18,050 --> 00:25:21,320
[Bonjour Green Barley Choux]

501
00:25:25,391 --> 00:25:29,194
[Place The Craquelin Onto The Frozen Dough]

502
00:25:29,661 --> 00:25:33,599
[Craquelin A Thin, Crunchy Cookie Layer Placed On Top]

503
00:25:34,333 --> 00:25:38,003
[Once Baked, It Will Transform
Into A Crisp, Golden Crust]

504
00:25:47,646 --> 00:25:51,583
[Make A Hole At The Bottom For The Filling]

505
00:25:56,088 --> 00:25:57,923
[Green Barley Cream]

506
00:25:57,923 --> 00:25:59,858
[Prepare The Cream]

507
00:26:01,193 --> 00:26:05,798
[Fill Each Puff With 80g
Of Green Barley Cream]

508
00:26:06,465 --> 00:26:10,235
[After Smoothing Out The Cream]

509
00:26:11,036 --> 00:26:13,639
[Top With Green Barley Powdered Sugar]

510
00:26:18,811 --> 00:26:21,246
Green Barley Choux!

511
00:26:21,246 --> 00:26:23,782
Vanilla Choux.

512
00:26:24,416 --> 00:26:26,151
Is that sugar?

513
00:26:26,151 --> 00:26:27,386
- Yes.
- I think so.

514
00:26:27,386 --> 00:26:28,520
My goodness.

515
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:30,522
[Magnifying Glass]
They put this for us to use.

516
00:26:30,522 --> 00:26:32,891
- You're right.
- In case we can't see clearly.

517
00:26:32,891 --> 00:26:34,593
Let me see that.

518
00:26:34,593 --> 00:26:36,261
These flowers are pretty.

519
00:26:36,261 --> 00:26:37,896
Look how pretty they are.

520
00:26:37,896 --> 00:26:39,965
They're really pretty.

521
00:26:39,965 --> 00:26:41,235
You can see them closely.

522
00:26:41,235 --> 00:26:43,949
They look prettier up close.

523
00:26:45,104 --> 00:26:48,574
My granddaughter just started third grade.

524
00:26:48,574 --> 00:26:52,845
She was elected class president,
so we came to celebrate.

525
00:26:52,845 --> 00:26:53,979
Congratulations.

526
00:26:53,979 --> 00:26:56,181
You look like a smart girl.

527
00:26:56,181 --> 00:26:57,783
Your grandma must be proud.

528
00:26:57,783 --> 00:26:59,384
[Wants To Show Off]

529
00:26:59,384 --> 00:27:02,988
Did you present them one at a time?

530
00:27:02,988 --> 00:27:04,890
- What about girls?
- I was Candidate Number One.

531
00:27:04,890 --> 00:27:07,159
- Number one?
- Yes.

532
00:27:07,159 --> 00:27:10,529
Did everyone present their pledges?

533
00:27:10,529 --> 00:27:12,264
- Fair and square?
- Yes.

534
00:27:12,264 --> 00:27:16,668
And you ended up with seven votes?

535
00:27:16,668 --> 00:27:17,910
Yes.

536
00:27:18,604 --> 00:27:20,472
[Proud]

537
00:27:20,472 --> 00:27:23,041
Were you afraid you wouldn't win?

538
00:27:23,041 --> 00:27:25,811
As soon as I got my first vote,

539
00:27:25,811 --> 00:27:28,213
my heart was racing.

540
00:27:28,213 --> 00:27:30,082
Really?

541
00:27:30,082 --> 00:27:33,218
[Nervous Just Thinking About It]

542
00:27:33,218 --> 00:27:35,687
- Thank you very much.
- You're welcome.

543
00:27:35,687 --> 00:27:37,289
Thank you.

544
00:27:37,289 --> 00:27:39,725
- I'll go get your coffee.
- Okay.

545
00:27:40,559 --> 00:27:41,994
[4 Caffè Lattes]

546
00:27:41,994 --> 00:27:44,997
[2 Bonjour Green Barley Choux
2 Bonjour Vanilla Choux]

547
00:27:46,665 --> 00:27:48,500
Let's do half and half.

548
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:50,302
- We should try everything.
- That's right.

549
00:27:50,302 --> 00:27:51,637
[Sharing Equally]

550
00:27:52,104 --> 00:27:54,273
This looks like ice cream.

551
00:27:54,273 --> 00:27:57,276
- It really is like ice cream.
- I wonder if it will taste good.

552
00:28:00,379 --> 00:28:02,948
My fork won't go inside.

553
00:28:02,948 --> 00:28:04,483
I'll use my hands.

554
00:28:04,483 --> 00:28:06,518
[Laughing]

555
00:28:07,019 --> 00:28:11,256
[Everyone Starts Using Their Hands]

556
00:28:21,433 --> 00:28:24,269
I thought it was a steamed bun.

557
00:28:24,269 --> 00:28:27,773
I figured I could get some to go.

558
00:28:27,773 --> 00:28:32,578
I thought it was steamed buns, too.

559
00:28:32,578 --> 00:28:34,079
Think about the past.

560
00:28:34,580 --> 00:28:36,268
Back in the day,

561
00:28:36,848 --> 00:28:40,919
Mother worked hard to afford steamed buns,

562
00:28:40,919 --> 00:28:44,590
only to give them to her kids.

563
00:28:44,590 --> 00:28:47,326
[Delicious Food]
I think about how she must've wanted them.

564
00:28:47,326 --> 00:28:48,560
[Brings Someone Special To Mind]

565
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:49,884
Congratulations.

566
00:28:50,395 --> 00:28:52,231
- Thank you.
- Little miss.

567
00:28:52,764 --> 00:28:54,866
- Thank you.
- Little miss.

568
00:28:54,866 --> 00:28:56,702
[Sharing Dessert With Loved Ones]

569
00:28:56,702 --> 00:28:59,638
[Takes A Picture]
This is a description of the dessert.

570
00:29:00,872 --> 00:29:03,642
[Grandma Takes A Bite]

571
00:29:03,642 --> 00:29:08,146
[Granddaughter Takes A Bite]

572
00:29:08,146 --> 00:29:09,519
It's good.

573
00:29:20,525 --> 00:29:24,062
[The Afternoon Menu Is A Huge Hit]

574
00:29:24,062 --> 00:29:28,567
[Current Time Is 12 p.m.]

575
00:29:29,635 --> 00:29:33,171
[Current Temperature Is 13 Celsius]

576
00:29:33,171 --> 00:29:36,341
[Current Body Temperature]

577
00:29:36,341 --> 00:29:38,477
- I have a slight fever. I should go home.
- Is that so?

578
00:29:38,477 --> 00:29:39,745
I have a slight fever.

579
00:29:39,745 --> 00:29:40,812
[I Worked Hard]

580
00:29:43,248 --> 00:29:45,817
[Front Row Seats To Dino's Latte-Making]

581
00:29:45,817 --> 00:29:47,336
That's a work of art.

582
00:29:50,756 --> 00:29:51,990
Oh, my.

583
00:29:51,990 --> 00:29:53,651
Hello.

584
00:29:53,651 --> 00:29:55,386
Welcome.

585
00:29:56,461 --> 00:29:59,231
First off, thank you for coming.

586
00:29:59,231 --> 00:30:04,636
- You can enter only with someone over 65.
- Yes.

587
00:30:04,636 --> 00:30:06,805
- Are you over 65?
- Yes.

588
00:30:06,805 --> 00:30:11,543
I apologize, but may I see your ID?
It's the rule.

589
00:30:11,543 --> 00:30:13,712
I was registered later.

590
00:30:13,712 --> 00:30:15,714
[Registered Late But Still Made It]
I see.

591
00:30:15,714 --> 00:30:18,784
We have a table for five over there.

592
00:30:18,784 --> 00:30:20,610
- Thank you.
- Please have a seat.

593
00:30:24,556 --> 00:30:26,551
- Yes?
- You can order.

594
00:30:26,551 --> 00:30:28,560
One orangeade.

595
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:30,429
One Americano...

596
00:30:30,429 --> 00:30:32,230
- One Americano.
- Make it hot, please.

597
00:30:32,230 --> 00:30:33,665
What did Grandma want?

598
00:30:33,665 --> 00:30:35,634
One lemon honey tea.

599
00:30:35,634 --> 00:30:37,636
Green Barley Field Tart.

600
00:30:37,636 --> 00:30:39,137
Vanilla Choux.

601
00:30:39,137 --> 00:30:41,106
One Vanilla Choux.

602
00:30:41,106 --> 00:30:42,541
- One Green Barley Choux.
- Let's eat plenty.

603
00:30:42,541 --> 00:30:44,109
- Green Barley Choux?
- Yes.

604
00:30:44,109 --> 00:30:45,344
One baguette.

605
00:30:45,344 --> 00:30:46,912
And one of these.

606
00:30:46,912 --> 00:30:49,147
- One Cha Loaf Bread?
- Yes.

607
00:30:49,147 --> 00:30:50,949
[Taking Notes]

608
00:30:50,949 --> 00:30:53,418
We've been starving for days.

609
00:30:53,418 --> 00:30:55,987
You should enjoy as much as you can.

610
00:30:55,987 --> 00:30:57,369
They're great.

611
00:30:57,923 --> 00:30:59,326
Hee Ae.

612
00:30:59,326 --> 00:31:02,327
Table five ordered a lot of stuff.

613
00:31:02,327 --> 00:31:05,163
- I'll write it here.
- Okay.

614
00:31:05,163 --> 00:31:07,632
- Orangeade, lemon tea...
- Lemon...

615
00:31:07,632 --> 00:31:09,000
- Lemon honey tea.
- Yes.

616
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:13,138
- Can you help me with that?
- Of course.

617
00:31:13,138 --> 00:31:14,806
Also, a baguette.

618
00:31:15,574 --> 00:31:18,016
I've become much smarter.

619
00:31:21,713 --> 00:31:23,762
Orangeade.

620
00:31:25,717 --> 00:31:26,852
[I, Kim Hee Ae,]

621
00:31:26,852 --> 00:31:30,048
[May Be Busy But I'll Be Calm And Careful]

622
00:31:32,324 --> 00:31:35,920
[Rushing Doesn't Help Things]

623
00:31:37,496 --> 00:31:40,832
[True Elegance Starts With]

624
00:31:40,832 --> 00:31:44,724
[Staying True To Your Own Pace]

625
00:31:46,037 --> 00:31:50,275
[Instead Of Matching The World's Pace]

626
00:31:50,275 --> 00:31:53,508
[Make The World Move To Yours]

627
00:31:54,446 --> 00:31:55,781
Take your time.

628
00:31:55,781 --> 00:31:57,315
I will.

629
00:31:57,315 --> 00:32:01,186
[See? They Want You To Slow Down]

630
00:32:01,186 --> 00:32:03,054
- Kitchen team?
- Yes?

631
00:32:03,054 --> 00:32:06,806
- Please slice this up and toast it.
- Got it.

632
00:32:19,504 --> 00:32:21,606
One orangeade.

633
00:32:21,606 --> 00:32:24,976
- Over here, please.
- For the little miss.

634
00:32:24,976 --> 00:32:26,311
Thank you.

635
00:32:27,279 --> 00:32:28,747
This is lemon honey tea.

636
00:32:28,747 --> 00:32:30,749
- Can someone hand it over?
- I'll hand it over.

637
00:32:32,818 --> 00:32:35,053
You're really beautiful.

638
00:32:35,754 --> 00:32:37,712
Thank you.

639
00:32:38,356 --> 00:32:40,826
It's our first day, so things are hectic.

640
00:32:40,826 --> 00:32:42,294
That's even better.

641
00:32:42,294 --> 00:32:43,428
- Please enjoy.
- Yes.

642
00:32:43,428 --> 00:32:45,035
Thank you.

643
00:32:57,309 --> 00:32:59,110
- This...
- I'll bring the knife.

644
00:32:59,110 --> 00:33:00,312
[Warm Toasted Baguette]

645
00:33:09,888 --> 00:33:11,456
- Table five.
- Table five?

646
00:33:11,456 --> 00:33:14,493
- Do you want me to carry one?
- Thank you.

647
00:33:14,493 --> 00:33:15,844
It's on your face.

648
00:33:18,063 --> 00:33:19,531
One Vanilla Choux.

649
00:33:19,531 --> 00:33:21,032
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

650
00:33:21,032 --> 00:33:22,701
Green Barley Choux.

651
00:33:23,301 --> 00:33:25,796
That looks delicious. Thank you.

652
00:33:27,839 --> 00:33:29,674
- Here's your Green Barley Field Tart.
- Thank you.

653
00:33:29,674 --> 00:33:31,243
- This one's really good.
- It's so cute.

654
00:33:31,243 --> 00:33:32,513
Thank you.

655
00:33:32,513 --> 00:33:36,481
[The Essence Of Beautiful, Verdant Gochang]

656
00:33:36,481 --> 00:33:39,857
[In A Single Dessert]

657
00:33:40,485 --> 00:33:43,421
[Embracing Gochang
Bonjour Green Barley Tart]

658
00:33:45,290 --> 00:33:46,291
[Nods]

659
00:33:46,291 --> 00:33:47,993
This was a good choice.

660
00:33:47,993 --> 00:33:49,761
[Licking The Fork As Well]

661
00:33:53,131 --> 00:33:54,566
[Takes A Big Bite As Well]

662
00:33:54,566 --> 00:33:55,634
Is it green barley?

663
00:33:55,634 --> 00:33:57,369
What does it taste like?

664
00:33:57,369 --> 00:33:58,812
- Like barley.
- Yes.

665
00:34:02,207 --> 00:34:04,543
They must've made everything here.

666
00:34:07,879 --> 00:34:10,775
[Yes, He's Making Everything]

667
00:34:17,055 --> 00:34:20,401
[A Mountain Of Mugwort Sponge Cake]

668
00:34:22,227 --> 00:34:26,737
[A Path Of Almond Crumble
That Invites You For A Stroll]

669
00:34:29,901 --> 00:34:32,604
[A Final Touch Of Gold]

670
00:34:32,604 --> 00:34:33,939
This is really good.

671
00:34:37,642 --> 00:34:40,145
- This is really delicious.
- It's good, right?

672
00:34:42,814 --> 00:34:44,583
It's very moist.

673
00:34:44,583 --> 00:34:45,717
Very moist.

674
00:34:45,717 --> 00:34:49,854
[Trying The Other Desserts]

675
00:34:53,391 --> 00:34:55,460
Me first.

676
00:34:55,460 --> 00:34:57,028
You take that one, Mom.

677
00:34:57,028 --> 00:34:58,847
- Give me a piece.
- Have the biggest one.

678
00:35:06,471 --> 00:35:08,040
They're all delicious.

679
00:35:11,509 --> 00:35:15,313
Good thing you tagged along
with your grandpa.

680
00:35:15,313 --> 00:35:19,384
My age came in handy for once.

681
00:35:19,384 --> 00:35:23,154
[You Must Be Over 65 Years Old To Enter]

682
00:35:23,154 --> 00:35:27,959
[Bonjour Bakery

683
00:35:49,781 --> 00:35:50,915
Here's your receipt.

684
00:35:50,915 --> 00:35:52,417
If you wait a moment...

685
00:35:52,417 --> 00:35:53,818
Welcome.

686
00:35:53,818 --> 00:35:55,587
Hello.

687
00:35:55,587 --> 00:35:57,822
[Glad To See You]
You came all the way to the countryside.

688
00:36:47,505 --> 00:36:48,973
Hello.

689
00:36:49,774 --> 00:36:51,643
- Welcome.
- I'm your neighbor.

690
00:36:51,643 --> 00:36:52,544
You are?

691
00:36:52,544 --> 00:36:55,914
- You guys came all this way.
- We did.

692
00:36:55,914 --> 00:36:57,916
At least I get to meet you.

693
00:36:57,916 --> 00:37:00,251
- Yes.
- What an honored guest.

694
00:37:00,251 --> 00:37:01,686
Thank you.

695
00:37:01,686 --> 00:37:03,555
Why didn't you come sooner?

696
00:37:03,555 --> 00:37:04,823
You took a while.

697
00:37:04,823 --> 00:37:05,890
Were you busy?

698
00:37:05,890 --> 00:37:09,527
I looked outside this morning
and saw people bustling.

699
00:37:09,527 --> 00:37:12,063
I waited, but the place got too crowded.

700
00:37:13,732 --> 00:37:15,533
What time do you close?

701
00:37:15,533 --> 00:37:17,669
Around 6 or 7?

702
00:37:17,669 --> 00:37:20,338
I heard there are a lot of people.

703
00:37:20,338 --> 00:37:23,141
I'm surprised people came all this way.

704
00:37:23,141 --> 00:37:26,010
- Yes, a lot of people showed up.
- They sure did.

705
00:37:27,145 --> 00:37:31,082
[When Things Slowed Down]

706
00:37:31,082 --> 00:37:34,753
[She Made Her Way To The Bakery]

707
00:37:34,753 --> 00:37:36,187
I'm glad you came.

708
00:37:36,187 --> 00:37:37,489
Thank you.

709
00:37:37,489 --> 00:37:39,224
What's this?

710
00:37:39,224 --> 00:37:40,458
It's chamomile tea.

711
00:37:40,458 --> 00:37:42,227
- Is it tea?
- It's better for you than coffee.

712
00:37:42,227 --> 00:37:43,895
- You're right.
- Okay.

713
00:37:43,895 --> 00:37:46,030
- It will help with your sleep.
- Okay.

714
00:37:46,030 --> 00:37:47,432
The choux is very good.

715
00:37:47,432 --> 00:37:49,701
- I'll take one.
- You should get this one.

716
00:37:50,435 --> 00:37:52,270
[Bonjour Green Barley Choux]
The ladies like this one.

717
00:37:52,270 --> 00:37:55,106
- You should get that.
- I'll take this.

718
00:37:55,874 --> 00:37:58,176
[Bonjour Vanilla Choux]]
I'll get this to go.

719
00:37:58,176 --> 00:37:59,944
- All right.
- My husband is sick.

720
00:37:59,944 --> 00:38:02,113
- Pardon?
- My husband couldn't come.

721
00:38:02,113 --> 00:38:03,529
I see.

722
00:38:04,749 --> 00:38:06,985
I have to let him try it.

723
00:38:06,985 --> 00:38:09,287
Wives are always like this.

724
00:38:09,287 --> 00:38:12,690
- Meanwhile, husbands always forget.
- No, not mine.

725
00:38:12,690 --> 00:38:14,859
My husband thinks of me. This one.

726
00:38:14,859 --> 00:38:16,261
He looks out for you?

727
00:38:16,261 --> 00:38:18,496
- Yes, all the time.
- My goodness.

728
00:38:18,496 --> 00:38:19,764
[1 Chamomile Tea]

729
00:38:19,764 --> 00:38:22,167
He's very kind. One Vanilla Choux.

730
00:38:22,167 --> 00:38:23,835
One Green Barley Choux.

731
00:38:23,835 --> 00:38:25,737
- Yes, that's it.
- Thank you.

732
00:38:25,737 --> 00:38:27,939
It's so nice to meet you.

733
00:38:27,939 --> 00:38:29,641
It's nice to meet you.

734
00:38:29,641 --> 00:38:31,176
You don't know us.

735
00:38:31,176 --> 00:38:32,443
But we know you.

736
00:38:32,443 --> 00:38:34,345
No, I'm glad to meet you too.

737
00:38:37,182 --> 00:38:41,486
[A New Customer Arrives]

738
00:38:41,486 --> 00:38:43,655
- Hello.
- Hello.

739
00:38:43,655 --> 00:38:44,956
Hello.

740
00:38:44,956 --> 00:38:47,525
You should have a seat inside that room.

741
00:38:47,525 --> 00:38:49,506
Just a moment, please.

742
00:38:50,562 --> 00:38:53,932
Should I move to that seat?

743
00:38:53,932 --> 00:38:55,200
Pardon?

744
00:38:55,934 --> 00:38:59,950
I don't need a table for four.

745
00:39:01,272 --> 00:39:03,441
I realized it after I sat.

746
00:39:05,710 --> 00:39:08,000
I should sit here instead.

747
00:39:39,944 --> 00:39:41,832
How is it?

748
00:39:43,681 --> 00:39:45,750
- It's delicious.
- Isn't it?

749
00:39:45,750 --> 00:39:47,051
- Yes.
- Good.

750
00:39:47,051 --> 00:39:48,631
You made a good choice.

751
00:40:14,345 --> 00:40:17,348
[When The Bakery Became Busy Again]

752
00:40:17,348 --> 00:40:20,051
[She Gulped Down The Chamomile Tea]

753
00:40:20,952 --> 00:40:23,554
[Then People Watched For A While]

754
00:40:31,829 --> 00:40:34,399
Would you like to pay? This way, please.

755
00:40:34,866 --> 00:40:36,768
I'll leave so you get more customers.

756
00:40:36,768 --> 00:40:38,462
[But It's Okay]

757
00:40:39,063 --> 00:40:40,538
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

758
00:40:40,538 --> 00:40:42,507
- Take care.
- Bye.

759
00:40:42,507 --> 00:40:44,342
- Thank you.
- See you again.

760
00:40:44,342 --> 00:40:46,911
I might come again tomorrow.

761
00:40:46,911 --> 00:40:48,713
[Please Come Again!]

762
00:41:06,449 --> 00:41:08,199
I'll cut it for you.

763
00:41:08,199 --> 00:41:10,802
It's really good.
But I haven't tried that one.

764
00:41:14,939 --> 00:41:16,528
This one's good too.

765
00:41:17,775 --> 00:41:19,444
- It's delicious.
- What?

766
00:41:19,444 --> 00:41:20,845
It's good.

767
00:41:20,845 --> 00:41:22,551
There were lots of customers.

768
00:41:23,314 --> 00:41:25,083
I also saw kids at the front.

769
00:41:25,083 --> 00:41:27,285
People came with their grandchildren.

770
00:41:27,285 --> 00:41:28,786
There were couples.

771
00:41:28,786 --> 00:41:31,356
A group of four friends came together.

772
00:41:31,356 --> 00:41:34,692
[Telling Him All The Little Things]
Everyone was so friendly.

773
00:41:36,227 --> 00:41:37,500
Here.

774
00:41:43,301 --> 00:41:46,471
I was the first graduate from that school.

775
00:41:46,471 --> 00:41:48,272
The first and the seventh.

776
00:41:48,272 --> 00:41:49,407
I see.

777
00:41:49,407 --> 00:41:51,776
I think I liked him first.

778
00:41:51,776 --> 00:41:55,079
He looks like this now,
but he used to be handsome.

779
00:41:55,079 --> 00:41:58,516
- Back then...
- You'll be surprised at the old pictures.

780
00:41:58,516 --> 00:42:01,152
- His eyes were big.
- Back then, there was...

781
00:42:01,152 --> 00:42:03,688
But he got sick and ended up like this.

782
00:42:03,688 --> 00:42:06,991
[Changing The Subject]
There used to be a theater troupe here.

783
00:42:06,991 --> 00:42:10,328
I got sick in 1999.

784
00:42:10,328 --> 00:42:13,564
I had stage four gastric cancer,

785
00:42:13,564 --> 00:42:16,300
so I had surgery
at Seoul National University Hospital.

786
00:42:16,300 --> 00:42:21,873
I always feel sorry for her
because I'm constantly sick.

787
00:42:21,873 --> 00:42:26,344
She had a tough time looking after me.

788
00:42:26,344 --> 00:42:27,478
For example,

789
00:42:27,478 --> 00:42:30,715
he says I can't cry in front of him.

790
00:42:30,715 --> 00:42:36,154
I took a van to a quiet place
under the bridge.

791
00:42:36,154 --> 00:42:37,878
Near the river.

792
00:42:39,057 --> 00:42:42,960
I cried so much that day.

793
00:42:42,960 --> 00:42:44,595
Back then.

794
00:42:44,595 --> 00:42:47,999
Did the surgery go well? How are you now?

795
00:42:47,999 --> 00:42:50,234
Yes, I'm better now.

796
00:42:50,735 --> 00:42:53,905
I'm so happy.

797
00:42:53,905 --> 00:42:56,307
We decided to close our business.

798
00:42:56,307 --> 00:42:59,343
[Enjoys Baking]
I'm still pretty good at baking.

799
00:42:59,343 --> 00:43:01,245
Not like that, of course.

800
00:43:01,245 --> 00:43:03,075
Korean traditional pastry.

801
00:43:03,781 --> 00:43:06,984
These are noodle-style cookies.

802
00:43:07,652 --> 00:43:09,554
[Handmade Snacks]
I made all these.

803
00:43:09,554 --> 00:43:11,289
I didn't buy them.

804
00:43:11,289 --> 00:43:16,853
You must be happy to have a talented wife.

805
00:43:27,572 --> 00:43:30,208
[1 Hour Before Closing Time]

806
00:43:30,208 --> 00:43:31,809
- Hello.
- Hi.

807
00:43:31,809 --> 00:43:33,277
[New Customers Enter]
Hello.

808
00:43:33,277 --> 00:43:34,817
Welcome.

809
00:43:35,813 --> 00:43:37,648
- I've got it.
- Let me get this.

810
00:43:37,648 --> 00:43:39,517
[Walks Straight To The Showcase]

811
00:43:39,517 --> 00:43:42,620
They have tarts too.

812
00:43:42,620 --> 00:43:43,921
[Crowded Around The Desserts]
This one looks good.

813
00:43:43,921 --> 00:43:45,463
I'll wrap it for you.

814
00:43:46,224 --> 00:43:49,560
I'll try the cream brick.

815
00:43:49,560 --> 00:43:51,896
[4 Customers Take Their Seat]
It's pretty here.

816
00:43:53,831 --> 00:43:56,567
They're doing something for three days.

817
00:43:56,567 --> 00:43:58,302
A bakery or something.

818
00:43:58,302 --> 00:44:00,554
What's this for?

819
00:44:00,554 --> 00:44:01,606
Is it a prop?

820
00:44:01,606 --> 00:44:02,840
It's at every table.

821
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:04,375
[A Magnifying Glass At Every Table]
What's it for?

822
00:44:04,375 --> 00:44:06,711
Why this prop of all things?

823
00:44:06,711 --> 00:44:08,012
Just because.

824
00:44:08,012 --> 00:44:10,114
- Is it to get a closer look at the bread?
- That's not it.

825
00:44:10,114 --> 00:44:12,483
- Like this?
- We're elderly, right?

826
00:44:12,483 --> 00:44:15,186
For the menu?

827
00:44:15,186 --> 00:44:16,587
This is nice.

828
00:44:16,587 --> 00:44:18,778
[Likes It]
There's one on each table.

829
00:44:19,457 --> 00:44:23,194
I don't think they're over 65.

830
00:44:23,194 --> 00:44:25,043
I should ask first.

831
00:44:25,563 --> 00:44:28,299
Hello.

832
00:44:28,299 --> 00:44:29,433
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

833
00:44:29,433 --> 00:44:31,202
- Sorry to keep you waiting.
- It's okay.

834
00:44:31,202 --> 00:44:32,837
I'm sorry, but rules are rules.

835
00:44:32,837 --> 00:44:35,006
[A Must At Bonjour Bakery]
We have to check your IDs.

836
00:44:35,006 --> 00:44:36,607
[Puts Glasses On]

837
00:44:39,777 --> 00:44:41,345
- What are you doing?
- Big sis.

838
00:44:41,345 --> 00:44:42,380
- Thank you.
- Here you go.

839
00:44:42,380 --> 00:44:44,815
- What are you doing?
- Here you go, big sis.

840
00:44:44,815 --> 00:44:46,250
She called me big sis.

841
00:44:46,250 --> 00:44:48,913
[ID Check Complete]
Here you are, big bro.

842
00:44:48,913 --> 00:44:50,421
This is Chef Cha.

843
00:44:50,421 --> 00:44:52,490
He made everything today.

844
00:44:52,490 --> 00:44:55,560
- Really?
- Yes, I made everything.

845
00:44:55,560 --> 00:44:57,028
Please recommend for us.

846
00:44:57,028 --> 00:44:59,297
- What's good today?
- Today,

847
00:44:59,297 --> 00:45:01,899
a lot of people ordered the choux.

848
00:45:01,899 --> 00:45:06,743
It's made with the green barley from here.

849
00:45:06,743 --> 00:45:09,661
I recommend that one.

850
00:45:09,661 --> 00:45:10,741
Okay.

851
00:45:10,741 --> 00:45:12,977
I suggested the choux

852
00:45:12,977 --> 00:45:15,213
since everyone loves it.

853
00:45:15,213 --> 00:45:16,647
- Stay here.
- Why?

854
00:45:16,647 --> 00:45:18,249
Don't go.

855
00:45:18,249 --> 00:45:19,350
Are you scared?

856
00:45:19,350 --> 00:45:21,819
They like seeing you here.

857
00:45:21,819 --> 00:45:23,087
I guess.

858
00:45:23,087 --> 00:45:25,659
Stay here if you're not too busy.

859
00:45:25,659 --> 00:45:27,554
Okay, I will.

860
00:45:28,492 --> 00:45:30,228
[Reliable]

861
00:45:30,228 --> 00:45:35,533
[Chef Cha's Recommendation]
Why don't we get these two and share them?

862
00:45:35,533 --> 00:45:37,468
I'm curious about the tart.

863
00:45:37,468 --> 00:45:38,769
Let's get one.

864
00:45:38,769 --> 00:45:40,071
Yes, something new.

865
00:45:40,071 --> 00:45:41,739
They used mugwort.

866
00:45:41,739 --> 00:45:43,207
Let's get tart and...

867
00:45:43,207 --> 00:45:44,709
This one from before.

868
00:45:44,709 --> 00:45:46,811
It's Crème Brûlée.

869
00:45:46,811 --> 00:45:48,212
- Are you ready to order?
- Yes.

870
00:45:48,212 --> 00:45:49,247
Okay.

871
00:45:49,247 --> 00:45:52,149
- I think his name tag says, Dito.
- You should come.

872
00:45:52,149 --> 00:45:54,352
It says Dito.

873
00:45:54,352 --> 00:45:58,055
[Dito Goes To Take Their Order]

874
00:45:58,055 --> 00:45:59,690
One orangeade, please.

875
00:45:59,690 --> 00:46:01,259
Okay, one orangeade.

876
00:46:01,259 --> 00:46:02,293
Hot Americano.

877
00:46:02,293 --> 00:46:03,361
Hot chamomile tea.

878
00:46:03,361 --> 00:46:04,562
One tart.

879
00:46:04,562 --> 00:46:06,197
- One Crème Brûlée?
- Yes, please.

880
00:46:06,197 --> 00:46:08,032
- One Vanilla Choux.
- Vanilla Choux.

881
00:46:08,032 --> 00:46:10,601
- One Green Barley Choux.
- We're getting so much.

882
00:46:10,601 --> 00:46:12,003
- You picked the good ones.
- I'm sorry.

883
00:46:12,003 --> 00:46:14,205
- It's okay.
- One Cha Loaf Bread.

884
00:46:14,205 --> 00:46:15,373
One baguette.

885
00:46:15,373 --> 00:46:18,843
- One Cha Loaf Bread.
- This is our dinner.

886
00:46:18,843 --> 00:46:20,711
- One baguette.
- One baguette.

887
00:46:20,711 --> 00:46:22,179
Thank you.

888
00:46:22,179 --> 00:46:24,582
It doesn't suit the countryside.

889
00:46:24,582 --> 00:46:26,217
[New Customers Enter]
I think it does.

890
00:46:26,217 --> 00:46:27,251
Welcome.

891
00:46:27,251 --> 00:46:28,869
Hello.

892
00:46:35,593 --> 00:46:37,662
Nice magnifying glass.

893
00:46:39,664 --> 00:46:43,134
This place looks incredible.

894
00:46:43,134 --> 00:46:46,637
[Stare]

895
00:46:46,637 --> 00:46:50,941
[A Grandma Passes By The Bakery]

896
00:46:50,941 --> 00:46:55,112
She's the original owner of this place.

897
00:46:55,112 --> 00:47:00,885
[How's The Business Going?]

898
00:47:00,885 --> 00:47:05,323
- This used to be a corner store.
- Yes, I remember her.

899
00:47:06,791 --> 00:47:08,459
[They Remember The Corner Store]

900
00:47:08,459 --> 00:47:10,728
They made this place look incredible.

901
00:47:11,462 --> 00:47:12,730
Hello.

902
00:47:12,730 --> 00:47:15,199
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

903
00:47:15,199 --> 00:47:17,068
- Take your time.
- Okay.

904
00:47:17,068 --> 00:47:18,903
Do we order at the counter?

905
00:47:18,903 --> 00:47:21,105
- We'll come take your order.
- Okay.

906
00:47:22,073 --> 00:47:25,776
Should we get the Sweet Potato Cake?

907
00:47:25,776 --> 00:47:29,046
[Looking Over The Menu]
We have to take home any leftovers.

908
00:47:29,880 --> 00:47:33,351
[10 Items Need To Be Served]

909
00:47:33,351 --> 00:47:35,119
Green Barley Choux, Vanilla Choux.

910
00:47:35,119 --> 00:47:37,588
[Spotted Ki Taek]

911
00:47:37,588 --> 00:47:40,191
Can I talk to you casually?

912
00:47:40,191 --> 00:47:41,225
Please go ahead.

913
00:47:41,225 --> 00:47:42,426
You can speak casually.

914
00:47:42,426 --> 00:47:44,795
Can you please help me, Ki Taek?

915
00:47:44,795 --> 00:47:46,430
What do you need?

916
00:47:46,430 --> 00:47:48,899
There are a lot of desserts to serve.

917
00:47:48,899 --> 00:47:51,235
- I just take them out, right?
- Yes.

918
00:47:51,235 --> 00:47:56,307
[Coming To Dino's Rescue]

919
00:47:56,307 --> 00:47:58,709
- We're out of Crème Brûlée.
- I'll get more.

920
00:47:58,709 --> 00:48:00,111
- Do we have them?
- We should have some.

921
00:48:00,111 --> 00:48:01,622
Thank you.

922
00:48:04,382 --> 00:48:07,184
We need one Crème Brûlée, Seung Won.

923
00:48:07,184 --> 00:48:11,675
- I want you to use the torch.
- Got it.

924
00:48:12,123 --> 00:48:16,894
[While Ki Taek Makes The Crème Brûlée]

925
00:48:18,062 --> 00:48:22,266
[A Big Group Is Waiting]

926
00:48:23,167 --> 00:48:28,305
[Dino Quickly Makes The Drinks]

927
00:48:28,839 --> 00:48:31,942
- Here are your drinks.
- Thank you.

928
00:48:31,942 --> 00:48:34,712
- Here's a straw for your orangeade.
- Thanks.

929
00:48:34,712 --> 00:48:35,713
All right.

930
00:48:36,247 --> 00:48:38,349
Is this the sugar?

931
00:48:38,349 --> 00:48:39,750
- How many do you want?
- What is this?

932
00:48:39,750 --> 00:48:41,218
- Two?
- Is this soap?

933
00:48:41,218 --> 00:48:43,454
- I need more.
- You do?

934
00:48:43,454 --> 00:48:44,922
[Has A Sweet Tooth]

935
00:48:44,922 --> 00:48:48,092
You don't gain weight
even when you eat like this.

936
00:48:48,092 --> 00:48:50,261
[While They Enjoy Their Drinks]

937
00:48:51,128 --> 00:48:55,166
[Ki Taek Is Making The Crème Brûlée]

938
00:48:55,166 --> 00:48:58,068
[His First Time Making Crème Brûlée]

939
00:48:58,068 --> 00:49:02,273
[Spread The Sugar Evenly]

940
00:49:02,740 --> 00:49:06,844
[Get The Torch Ready]

941
00:49:08,412 --> 00:49:12,216
[Top It With A Caramel Layer]

942
00:49:12,950 --> 00:49:16,654
[And Sous Chef Ki Taek's Very First
Crème Brûlée Is Complete]

943
00:49:19,623 --> 00:49:24,895
You should crack the top and eat it.

944
00:49:24,895 --> 00:49:27,571
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

945
00:49:28,332 --> 00:49:30,968
[Dessert Successfully Served]

946
00:49:31,635 --> 00:49:34,638
He said to crack it like this.

947
00:49:34,638 --> 00:49:37,425
[Takes A Bite]
The cream inside looks delicious.

948
00:49:38,576 --> 00:49:40,044
This one is good.

949
00:49:40,044 --> 00:49:41,679
It looks great.

950
00:49:41,679 --> 00:49:43,447
[Satisfied Groans]

951
00:49:43,447 --> 00:49:44,515
It's good.

952
00:49:44,515 --> 00:49:46,016
[2 Orangeade
1 Bonjour Sweet Potato Cake]

953
00:49:46,016 --> 00:49:47,518
[1 Bonjour Citron Madeleine]

954
00:49:47,518 --> 00:49:52,289
[The Father-Daughter Table Also Got Dessert]

955
00:49:52,289 --> 00:49:54,458
I thought it'd be bigger than this.

956
00:49:55,025 --> 00:49:56,594
It's tiny.

957
00:49:56,594 --> 00:49:58,257
Is it really that funny?

958
00:49:58,863 --> 00:50:01,494
- Was this made with sweet potato?
- Yes.

959
00:50:11,275 --> 00:50:14,278
[They Split The Citron Madeleine]

960
00:50:15,913 --> 00:50:17,982
You should come with your friend tomorrow.

961
00:50:23,754 --> 00:50:25,582
The cake is delicious.

962
00:50:26,690 --> 00:50:30,694
[Cleared The Plates]

963
00:50:31,395 --> 00:50:32,997
Welcome.

964
00:50:34,532 --> 00:50:35,933
Hello.

965
00:50:36,700 --> 00:50:37,868
Hello.

966
00:50:39,737 --> 00:50:42,940
- Hello.
- Welcome.

967
00:50:42,940 --> 00:50:45,042
[Bustling Bakery Before Closing]
Hello.

968
00:50:46,844 --> 00:50:48,979
This and a madeleine.

969
00:50:48,979 --> 00:50:51,248
- Madeleine.
- Get me a madeleine.

970
00:50:51,248 --> 00:50:52,616
What was the drink?

971
00:50:52,616 --> 00:50:53,851
Two orangeades.

972
00:50:53,851 --> 00:50:55,686
- Two orangeades are ready.
- Hee Ae.

973
00:50:55,686 --> 00:50:57,988
Okay, I'll serve the desserts.

974
00:50:57,988 --> 00:51:00,925
[The Chef Team Joins To Help Rush Hour]

975
00:51:01,725 --> 00:51:04,161
You ordered a Vanilla Choux, right?

976
00:51:09,767 --> 00:51:11,902
- Thank you.
- Please enjoy.

977
00:51:11,902 --> 00:51:13,237
We even got a cake.

978
00:51:13,904 --> 00:51:15,715
I don't think I need dinner.

979
00:51:16,640 --> 00:51:20,210
[The Sun Has Set]

980
00:51:21,111 --> 00:51:24,148
[And It's Time To Close The Bakery]

981
00:51:24,148 --> 00:51:25,570
Time to go.

982
00:51:29,620 --> 00:51:32,523
- That was great.
- Thank you.

983
00:51:32,523 --> 00:51:33,657
Thank you.

984
00:51:33,657 --> 00:51:35,593
- Good job today.
- It was delicious.

985
00:51:35,593 --> 00:51:36,911
Thank you.

986
00:51:37,661 --> 00:51:39,196
[The Customers Leave One By One]

987
00:51:39,196 --> 00:51:41,165
Good night.

988
00:51:41,165 --> 00:51:42,833
Thank you.

989
00:51:42,833 --> 00:51:44,501
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

990
00:51:45,336 --> 00:51:47,951
Thank you.

991
00:51:47,951 --> 00:51:49,039
That was great.

992
00:51:49,039 --> 00:51:51,008
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

993
00:51:51,008 --> 00:51:52,242
[The Last Customer Leaves]

994
00:52:06,624 --> 00:52:10,127
[We Are Closed]

995
00:52:11,362 --> 00:52:13,497
- You worked hard.
- Great job.

996
00:52:13,497 --> 00:52:16,400
[End Of Day One At Bonjour Bakery]

997
00:52:19,303 --> 00:52:21,065
I'm exhausted.

998
00:52:23,073 --> 00:52:25,209
You did such a great job.

999
00:52:25,209 --> 00:52:27,777
- Great job today.
- Good job.

1000
00:52:29,513 --> 00:52:31,081
- Unbelievable.
- Isn't it?

1001
00:52:31,081 --> 00:52:33,183
- Seriously.
- I lost my mind

1002
00:52:33,183 --> 00:52:36,723
when that big group came in.

1003
00:52:36,723 --> 00:52:38,689
I was so lost.

1004
00:52:38,689 --> 00:52:41,025
I was doing well until then.

1005
00:52:41,025 --> 00:52:42,828
Yes, same.

1006
00:52:43,594 --> 00:52:47,331
[The Bakery Is Closed
But There's Still Work To Do]

1007
00:52:47,331 --> 00:52:48,737
My goodness.

1008
00:53:09,853 --> 00:53:11,021
That's dangerous.

1009
00:53:11,021 --> 00:53:13,223
I think I can handle it.

1010
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:26,236
[Welcome To Dishwashing Hell]

1011
00:53:32,242 --> 00:53:36,313
[The Kitchen Isn't Done Either]

1012
00:53:42,553 --> 00:53:47,658
[Prepping For Tomorrow's Desserts]

1013
00:53:50,094 --> 00:53:51,328
Do you need my help?

1014
00:53:51,328 --> 00:53:52,730
- Yes.
- Okay.

1015
00:53:52,730 --> 00:53:54,364
[Shaping Green Barley Brioche Dough]

1016
00:54:02,239 --> 00:54:07,377
[Rounding The Dough After The First Rise]

1017
00:54:07,377 --> 00:54:11,215
[Removes Large Air Bubbles]

1018
00:54:11,215 --> 00:54:16,453
[And Creates A Smooth Surface]

1019
00:54:16,453 --> 00:54:17,454
Here you go.

1020
00:54:22,493 --> 00:54:28,499
[These Carefully Shaped Pieces]

1021
00:54:29,967 --> 00:54:32,469
[Will Wear A Green Hat]

1022
00:54:33,203 --> 00:54:35,773
[And Bake Until Plump]

1023
00:54:37,741 --> 00:54:40,511
[Something As Charming
As The Green Barley Choux]

1024
00:54:42,279 --> 00:54:46,250
[The Nutty Green Barley Brioche]

1025
00:54:46,250 --> 00:54:47,785
Great job today.

1026
00:54:47,785 --> 00:54:49,953
- Great work.
- Thanks for all your hard work.

1027
00:54:49,953 --> 00:54:52,256
- Great job.
- It was hectic.

1028
00:54:52,256 --> 00:54:55,359
I think we need one more person here.

1029
00:54:55,359 --> 00:54:57,861
- This is crazy.
- I agree.

1030
00:54:57,861 --> 00:55:01,431
You have a grandma and a kid working.

1031
00:55:01,431 --> 00:55:03,867
- It's our first day here.
- Really.

1032
00:55:03,867 --> 00:55:06,715
This was unbelievable.

1033
00:55:11,575 --> 00:55:13,844
Another day has passed.

1034
00:55:13,844 --> 00:55:16,213
- Yes.
- Still...

1035
00:55:16,213 --> 00:55:18,916
Despite everything, we did well.

1036
00:55:18,916 --> 00:55:20,918
We did great.

1037
00:55:20,918 --> 00:55:24,054
[Amateur 1 Gets Choked Up]
You have two amateurs here.

1038
00:55:25,222 --> 00:55:27,391
- Great job, guys.
- You too.

1039
00:55:27,391 --> 00:55:28,892
[Amateur 2 Walks In Right On Time]
Don't go anywhere.

1040
00:55:28,892 --> 00:55:30,460
- Don't go.
- Okay.

1041
00:55:30,460 --> 00:55:32,029
- Good job today.
- Hey, Dino.

1042
00:55:32,029 --> 00:55:33,197
Don't leave us.

1043
00:55:33,197 --> 00:55:36,600
- Okay, I won't.
- We need you here.

1044
00:55:36,600 --> 00:55:39,336
You're such a hard worker.

1045
00:55:39,336 --> 00:55:40,771
- Really...
- Good job, my boy.

1046
00:55:40,771 --> 00:55:42,014
Thank you.

1047
00:55:43,407 --> 00:55:45,809
- Hello.
- Hello.

1048
00:55:45,809 --> 00:55:48,278
- Thanks for coming all this way.
- Not at all.

1049
00:55:48,278 --> 00:55:49,513
[First Day At An Unfamiliar Bakery] Seventeen.

1050
00:55:49,513 --> 00:55:50,814
I feel so nervous.

1051
00:55:50,814 --> 00:55:52,216
Are you nervous?

1052
00:55:52,216 --> 00:55:53,550
I've never done a part-time job before.

1053
00:55:53,550 --> 00:55:55,352
[His First Part-Time Job]

1054
00:55:55,352 --> 00:55:58,088
[His First Time Extracting Coffee]
Just like that.

1055
00:55:59,189 --> 00:56:00,591
- That's it.
- This is hard.

1056
00:56:00,591 --> 00:56:04,294
If you're not used to it,
you have to move it from eight o'clock.

1057
00:56:04,294 --> 00:56:05,863
Welcome!

1058
00:56:05,863 --> 00:56:07,164
- Are you here alone?
- Yes.

1059
00:56:07,164 --> 00:56:09,333
[Cheerfully Greeting Customers]
Please sit wherever you like.

1060
00:56:09,333 --> 00:56:11,568
Is it a hot latte?

1061
00:56:11,568 --> 00:56:13,637
- Yes, please
- Okay.

1062
00:56:14,304 --> 00:56:17,374
[He Was A Bit Clumsy But Tried His Best]

1063
00:56:18,375 --> 00:56:20,277
This is hard.

1064
00:56:20,277 --> 00:56:21,712
Just a moment, please.

1065
00:56:23,180 --> 00:56:25,682
[He Was Running Around Busy All Day]

1066
00:56:25,682 --> 00:56:27,284
Sweet Potato Cake and Green Barley Tart...

1067
00:56:27,284 --> 00:56:29,052
They just need to go out.

1068
00:56:31,421 --> 00:56:36,360
[And Constantly Washing The Dishes]

1069
00:56:37,294 --> 00:56:39,363
- Thanks for your hard work.
- Sorry?

1070
00:56:39,363 --> 00:56:41,932
You were called in so suddenly.

1071
00:56:41,932 --> 00:56:43,200
Don't mention it.

1072
00:56:43,200 --> 00:56:46,370
Thank goodness you two came to help.

1073
00:56:46,370 --> 00:56:47,771
- Seriously.
- The dishes.

1074
00:56:47,771 --> 00:56:50,007
- We ran out of plates.
- Totally.

1075
00:56:50,007 --> 00:56:52,943
We would've been in trouble
without you two.

1076
00:56:52,943 --> 00:56:56,513
As soon as I came out,
I wanted to go back in.

1077
00:56:57,080 --> 00:57:00,684
[Chef Cha Mimicks Manager Kim]

1078
00:57:01,451 --> 00:57:04,554
[Embarrassed]

1079
00:57:06,356 --> 00:57:08,759
Are you done? What about them?

1080
00:57:08,759 --> 00:57:10,227
I'm going crazy.

1081
00:57:10,227 --> 00:57:12,162
I can't think right now.

1082
00:57:12,162 --> 00:57:14,164
I'm completely lost right now.

1083
00:57:14,164 --> 00:57:16,767
I'm so confused.

1084
00:57:16,767 --> 00:57:20,737
[99.99999% Synchronization]
I was totally overwhelmed.

1085
00:57:21,805 --> 00:57:23,740
- That was fun.
- To our first day.

1086
00:57:23,740 --> 00:57:25,575
- Great job.
- Great job, everyone.

1087
00:57:26,944 --> 00:57:29,980
[A Can Of Beer]

1088
00:57:29,980 --> 00:57:33,784
[After A Day Of Hard Work]

1089
00:57:40,791 --> 00:57:42,333
This is nice.

1090
00:57:43,327 --> 00:57:47,564
[Sharing A Moment
With The Team Who Worked Hard]

1091
00:57:48,365 --> 00:57:51,868
[But The Exhaustion Is Real]

1092
00:57:51,868 --> 00:57:53,770
Your hand is trembling.

1093
00:57:53,770 --> 00:57:55,339
Your hand is shaking.

1094
00:57:55,339 --> 00:57:56,666
[Difficult Day 1]

1095
00:57:56,666 --> 00:58:00,477
I'll try to go back and forth tomorrow.

1096
00:58:00,477 --> 00:58:01,979
You should go into the hall.

1097
00:58:01,979 --> 00:58:03,246
Yes, I will.

1098
00:58:03,246 --> 00:58:05,515
We need someone to do the dishes.

1099
00:58:05,515 --> 00:58:08,518
I agree wholeheartedly.

1100
00:58:08,518 --> 00:58:10,854
[One Question Comes To Mind]
You act like you'll be here tomorrow.

1101
00:58:10,854 --> 00:58:13,857
Why am I acting like this?

1102
00:58:13,857 --> 00:58:15,625
- I'm so invested.
- Yes.

1103
00:58:15,625 --> 00:58:18,228
He's talking like he's going to be here.

1104
00:58:18,228 --> 00:58:20,067
I keep forgetting.

1105
00:58:20,067 --> 00:58:22,570
[Hard To Let Him Go After Only One Day]
He's not here tomorrow.

1106
00:58:23,133 --> 00:58:28,205
I have to film content
starting tomorrow at noon.

1107
00:58:28,205 --> 00:58:29,373
[He Can't Help Tomorrow]

1108
00:58:29,373 --> 00:58:32,175
That's why I need to go back tonight.

1109
00:58:32,743 --> 00:58:36,013
[Disappointed]

1110
00:58:36,013 --> 00:58:37,147
I don't know.

1111
00:58:37,147 --> 00:58:39,282
Is it because we went through this?

1112
00:58:39,282 --> 00:58:40,751
I shouldn't say this,

1113
00:58:40,751 --> 00:58:42,268
but why do I feel...

1114
00:58:42,652 --> 00:58:44,014
a little...

1115
00:58:44,988 --> 00:58:46,522
Why do I feel...

1116
00:58:47,057 --> 00:58:48,502
a little...

1117
00:58:53,230 --> 00:58:55,298
I'm fond of him.

1118
00:58:55,298 --> 00:58:58,395
[Sudden Confession]
I've grown fond of him.

1119
00:58:58,395 --> 00:59:00,663
I wonder why.

1120
00:59:01,371 --> 00:59:03,573
He looks manly,

1121
00:59:03,573 --> 00:59:06,710
yet very pretty at the same time.

1122
00:59:06,710 --> 00:59:08,011
I kept thinking that.

1123
00:59:08,011 --> 00:59:09,203
Thank you.

1124
00:59:11,181 --> 00:59:14,351
I actually learned a lot from Hee Ae.

1125
00:59:14,351 --> 00:59:19,823
Someone ordered a vanilla latte,
then some sweet desserts.

1126
00:59:19,823 --> 00:59:24,428
I was just going to place the order,

1127
00:59:24,428 --> 00:59:25,962
[So Pretty]
but she said

1128
00:59:25,962 --> 00:59:28,899
two sweet items wouldn't pair well.

1129
00:59:29,417 --> 00:59:34,638
That showed me what real service means.

1130
00:59:34,638 --> 00:59:36,907
[Thoughtful Touch]
So that's how you serve customers.

1131
00:59:38,208 --> 00:59:39,763
I learned a lot.

1132
00:59:40,343 --> 00:59:42,079
Why didn't I think of that?

1133
00:59:43,293 --> 00:59:47,284
I was reminded once again
that real experience matters more.

1134
00:59:47,284 --> 00:59:49,553
- It's about experience.
- Once you do it,

1135
00:59:49,553 --> 00:59:52,081
it gets easier next time.

1136
00:59:53,890 --> 00:59:55,392
- Hey, Dino.
- Yes?

1137
00:59:55,392 --> 00:59:57,094
When are you going? Are you leaving now?

1138
00:59:57,094 --> 00:59:58,962
I think I should go now.

1139
00:59:58,962 --> 01:00:00,997
Now? Okay, then.

1140
01:00:00,997 --> 01:00:04,034
I really want to come again

1141
01:00:04,034 --> 01:00:06,490
if my schedule allows it.

1142
01:00:10,010 --> 01:00:14,615
[You're Always Welcome. Bye, Dino!]

1143
01:00:18,915 --> 01:00:21,084
[After The First Day]

1144
01:00:21,084 --> 01:00:24,621
[The Morning Of Day 2 Begins]

1145
01:00:28,992 --> 01:00:33,830
[The Day Begins In The Village]

1146
01:00:35,932 --> 01:00:39,936
[The Bonjour Family Greets Day 2]

1147
01:00:48,778 --> 01:00:51,982
[Seon Ho Wakes Up]

1148
01:00:56,853 --> 01:01:02,859
[Seon Ho Arrived Early Morning
After His Performance]

1149
01:01:10,667 --> 01:01:15,472
[Can He Tame This Hair?]

1150
01:01:20,477 --> 01:01:25,749
[Wakes Up And Gets Ready For Work]

1151
01:01:27,384 --> 01:01:30,587
[Ki Taek Wakes Up]

1152
01:01:38,395 --> 01:01:43,300
[The Impractical Guide To Hair]

1153
01:01:46,670 --> 01:01:48,905
- Did you sleep well?
- Yes.

1154
01:01:50,273 --> 01:01:51,975
It was nice and warm.

1155
01:01:51,975 --> 01:01:53,710
Yes, it was.

1156
01:01:53,710 --> 01:01:55,946
It was hot yesterday,

1157
01:01:55,946 --> 01:01:58,525
but warm at night.

1158
01:02:01,418 --> 01:02:03,587
Your cologne smells good.

1159
01:02:03,587 --> 01:02:05,322
Which one is it?

1160
01:02:05,322 --> 01:02:06,389
Do you want some?

1161
01:02:06,389 --> 01:02:08,363
No, it's okay.

1162
01:02:09,960 --> 01:02:13,597
[It Smells Good Because It's You]

1163
01:02:23,106 --> 01:02:25,663
I'm seeing a local for the first time.

1164
01:02:26,943 --> 01:02:28,745
He's working.

1165
01:02:30,947 --> 01:02:32,406
Hello.

1166
01:02:32,949 --> 01:02:35,785
We opened a café over there.

1167
01:02:35,785 --> 01:02:37,721
You should stop by.

1168
01:02:37,721 --> 01:02:39,362
Have a nice day.

1169
01:02:46,263 --> 01:02:49,119
He's here today. Is it the nice weather?

1170
01:02:53,670 --> 01:02:55,138
That looks great.

1171
01:02:55,138 --> 01:02:56,673
[Today's Menu]

1172
01:02:57,374 --> 01:02:58,875
Let's see.

1173
01:03:09,052 --> 01:03:14,224
[The Light Goes On At The Bakery For Day 2]

1174
01:03:23,333 --> 01:03:28,104
[Seon Ho Begins Preparing
For The Day With A Cup Of Coffee]

1175
01:03:49,526 --> 01:03:51,828
Oh, gosh.

1176
01:03:51,828 --> 01:03:54,331
We need to mop the floors.

1177
01:03:54,331 --> 01:03:55,632
This is really bad.

1178
01:03:55,632 --> 01:04:00,403
[Finds Traces Of Hard Work
From The First Day]

1179
01:04:45,949 --> 01:04:47,117
I'm here.

1180
01:04:48,451 --> 01:04:49,619
Good morning.

1181
01:04:49,619 --> 01:04:51,254
[Something's Different]

1182
01:04:53,390 --> 01:04:55,792
Did you start cleaning right away?

1183
01:04:55,792 --> 01:04:57,961
Of course, I'm in charge of the hall.

1184
01:04:58,561 --> 01:05:01,064
You know, today...

1185
01:05:02,532 --> 01:05:04,134
We need to get strawberries.

1186
01:05:04,134 --> 01:05:06,202
- That's today?
- Yes, so...

1187
01:05:06,202 --> 01:05:07,203
[Need Strawberries For Today's Menu]

1188
01:05:07,203 --> 01:05:08,671
Before we open,

1189
01:05:08,671 --> 01:05:10,940
[Ki Taek Checks The Time]
we should go get some.

1190
01:05:10,940 --> 01:05:12,842
Put down your bag and get ready.

1191
01:05:12,842 --> 01:05:15,178
- We don't have time for this.
- It was today.

1192
01:05:15,178 --> 01:05:18,014
[The Day Chef Cha Mentioned]
Yes, today's the day.

1193
01:05:18,715 --> 01:05:20,116
Are we going now?

1194
01:05:20,116 --> 01:05:21,384
Let's wait a little.

1195
01:05:21,384 --> 01:05:23,753
- Let me clean this.
- Okay.

1196
01:05:25,688 --> 01:05:27,056
Can you give me 15 minutes?

1197
01:05:27,056 --> 01:05:28,291
Okay.

1198
01:05:28,291 --> 01:05:30,026
[He Keeps Checking The Time]
Why?

1199
01:05:30,026 --> 01:05:31,094
To boil some eggs.

1200
01:05:31,094 --> 01:05:33,263
That's a good idea.

1201
01:05:33,263 --> 01:05:35,265
You're a great worker.

1202
01:05:35,965 --> 01:05:39,302
Do you want an iced or a hot Americano?

1203
01:05:39,302 --> 01:05:41,237
[Breakfast Makes Ki Taek Happy]
I'll have an iced Americano.

1204
01:05:41,237 --> 01:05:43,124
- Got it.
- Thanks.

1205
01:06:00,557 --> 01:06:02,505
Are the eggs boiling?

1206
01:06:03,126 --> 01:06:04,885
He's gone.

1207
01:06:08,998 --> 01:06:10,333
Where are the napkins?

1208
01:06:11,634 --> 01:06:13,803
How's the coffee?

1209
01:06:13,803 --> 01:06:16,105
It's really good.

1210
01:06:16,105 --> 01:06:17,664
You're like a robot.

1211
01:06:18,174 --> 01:06:20,210
I'm serious.

1212
01:06:20,210 --> 01:06:21,578
But I don't know.

1213
01:06:21,578 --> 01:06:22,946
It's nice when a handsome guy

1214
01:06:22,946 --> 01:06:25,415
hands me a drink in the morning.

1215
01:06:25,415 --> 01:06:27,517
You're in top shape today.

1216
01:06:27,517 --> 01:06:29,698
It'll be great for business.

1217
01:06:31,024 --> 01:06:32,300
Ki Taek.

1218
01:06:34,357 --> 01:06:35,880
He's gone again.

1219
01:06:36,726 --> 01:06:41,018
He disappears whenever I call him.

1220
01:06:51,641 --> 01:06:54,744
[How Many More Minutes?]

1221
01:07:00,016 --> 01:07:02,418
I pressed the wrong button.
I'll use my intuition.

1222
01:07:04,153 --> 01:07:07,257
[It's Probably More Delicious That Way]

1223
01:07:12,529 --> 01:07:13,596
- Is that it?
- Yes.

1224
01:07:13,596 --> 01:07:15,098
Do you want some?

1225
01:07:21,738 --> 01:07:23,417
It's boiled perfectly.

1226
01:07:24,040 --> 01:07:25,775
It's not easy to boil eggs.

1227
01:07:25,775 --> 01:07:27,944
It's actually really simple.

1228
01:07:30,117 --> 01:07:31,795
- It's good, right?
- Yes.

1229
01:07:32,448 --> 01:07:34,117
Shall we get the strawberries?

1230
01:07:34,117 --> 01:07:37,487
[Headed To The Strawberry Field After Breakfast]

1231
01:07:37,487 --> 01:07:39,092
Let's go.

1232
01:07:39,092 --> 01:07:44,164
[Preview Of Day 2 - 10:55 a.m.]

1233
01:07:45,461 --> 01:07:48,698
[Final Checks Before Opening

1234
01:07:57,040 --> 01:07:59,042
Would it be okay to use this plate?

1235
01:07:59,042 --> 01:08:01,621
This one seems a little small.

1236
01:08:03,646 --> 01:08:05,114
[Flustered]

1237
01:08:09,786 --> 01:08:11,422
I'm so sorry.

1238
01:08:17,794 --> 01:08:19,829
[Makes A Mistake]

1239
01:08:19,829 --> 01:08:21,531
Turn off the camera.

1240
01:08:22,932 --> 01:08:26,035
[11:00 a.m.]

1241
01:08:26,035 --> 01:08:27,236
All right.

1242
01:08:28,871 --> 01:08:31,541
[Has No Idea About The Kitchen]

1243
01:08:32,241 --> 01:08:34,777
[While The Opening Bell Rings Clearly]

1244
01:08:36,112 --> 01:08:39,382
[Customers Begin To Gather]

1245
01:08:39,382 --> 01:08:42,251
- It's cold.
- Should we go inside?

1246
01:08:42,251 --> 01:08:44,053
Leave that here before we head in.

1247
01:08:44,053 --> 01:08:45,321
[From The Elegant Sound]

1248
01:08:47,390 --> 01:08:48,925
They're here.

1249
01:08:48,925 --> 01:08:51,004
- Welcome.
- Hello.

1250
01:08:52,261 --> 01:08:53,830
Please sit here.

1251
01:08:53,830 --> 01:08:55,331
Are you a party of five?

1252
01:08:55,331 --> 01:08:56,666
Please go over there.

1253
01:08:56,666 --> 01:08:57,734
Over there.

1254
01:08:57,734 --> 01:08:59,535
Would you like to order?

1255
01:08:59,535 --> 01:09:01,170
What should we order?

1256
01:09:01,170 --> 01:09:02,505
What's good here?

1257
01:09:02,505 --> 01:09:05,642
Today, the Strawberry Éclair is good.

1258
01:09:05,642 --> 01:09:07,504
The strawberry is fresh.

1259
01:09:08,244 --> 01:09:10,480
[No Response]
How does that sound?

1260
01:09:10,480 --> 01:09:12,382
How about Sweet Potato Cake?

1261
01:09:12,382 --> 01:09:13,850
[Copy And Repeat]
Sweet Potato Cake?

1262
01:09:13,850 --> 01:09:15,656
Just get us something good.

1263
01:09:15,656 --> 01:09:16,819
Something good.

1264
01:09:16,819 --> 01:09:18,221
I've been around long enough to see this.

1265
01:09:18,221 --> 01:09:20,089
Good thing we stayed alive.

1266
01:09:20,089 --> 01:09:22,158
It's all over once you're dead.

1267
01:09:22,158 --> 01:09:23,960
[Amid The Juicy Chatter]

1268
01:09:23,960 --> 01:09:26,529
[A Delicate And Graceful Touch Emerges]
I'm not good at this.

1269
01:09:26,529 --> 01:09:29,766
[Please Understand ]
I don't want to ruin the cake.

1270
01:09:29,766 --> 01:09:33,002
I'll divide it into six equal pieces.

1271
01:09:33,002 --> 01:09:36,005
[I, Kim Hee Ae, Will Divide This For You]

1272
01:09:37,073 --> 01:09:39,075
[One Piece]

1273
01:09:39,075 --> 01:09:41,077
[Two Pieces]

1274
01:09:41,077 --> 01:09:43,179
[Three Pieces, Four Pieces]

1275
01:09:43,179 --> 01:09:46,783
[Five Pieces]

1276
01:09:47,350 --> 01:09:50,086
[And Finally, Six Pieces!]

1277
01:09:50,086 --> 01:09:51,688
No need to be nervous.

1278
01:09:51,688 --> 01:09:52,755
Right.

1279
01:09:52,755 --> 01:09:54,557
[How Will...]

1280
01:09:54,557 --> 01:09:56,859
- Do you like sweet potatoes?
- Yes.

1281
01:09:56,859 --> 01:09:59,028
[Manager Kim's Day Go At The Bakery?]

1282
01:10:04,867 --> 01:10:06,209
I'll cut this.

1283
01:10:13,810 --> 01:10:16,913
[Amazed]

1284
01:10:19,248 --> 01:10:21,317
Look how soft this choux is.

1285
01:10:24,687 --> 01:10:26,954
I love desserts.

1286
01:10:58,087 --> 01:10:59,993
I'll try the green barley one.

1287
01:11:08,564 --> 01:11:11,007
I've seen this ad.

1288
01:11:12,468 --> 01:11:14,303
- From the ad you were in.
- It's so good.

1289
01:11:14,303 --> 01:11:15,438
Isn't it?

1290
01:11:15,438 --> 01:11:17,440
I love this one, too.

1291
01:11:19,242 --> 01:11:24,247
Chefs need to be sensitive and smart.

1292
01:11:24,247 --> 01:11:26,127
They say baking is science.

1293
01:11:26,682 --> 01:11:31,124
We should call them professors, not chefs.

1294
01:11:31,124 --> 01:11:34,290
- Professors?
- Yes.

1295
01:11:34,290 --> 01:11:36,559
They did such a great job with these.

1296
01:11:36,559 --> 01:11:38,992
[A Masterpiece]
These are really incredible.

1297
01:11:45,635 --> 01:11:47,637
How is it? Isn't it amazing?

1298
01:11:47,637 --> 01:11:49,705
I'm not kidding.

1299
01:11:49,705 --> 01:11:51,174
It's really good.

1300
01:11:51,174 --> 01:11:53,910
It's in my top three favorite foods.

1301
01:11:53,910 --> 01:11:56,579
What were the other two?

1302
01:11:56,579 --> 01:11:58,481
What? The stale bread?

1303
01:11:58,481 --> 01:12:00,316
What are you talking about?

1304
01:12:00,316 --> 01:12:03,075
- Didn't you say top three?
- That's what you meant.

1305
01:12:15,035 --> 01:12:16,555
Wow, this is...
